"0#Simmons Leadership Conference|Thank you all so much for dedicating your time to recording videos showcasing the Simmons Leadership Conference that recently took place. These videos will be a great way to showcase to our humans why they should watch the recordings available and help direct them to the content that is not to be missed! Videos aren‚Äôt always easy so thank you for pushing yourselves out of your comfort zone and supporting us with this.\n\n1#Thank you for lending a hand!|Jill, I hope you know how much I appreciate your support, guidance, input, and allocated time across the last couple of weeks. Just when I think I know enough to be dangerous, navigating the org after 6 months, there's always something new around each corner. So thank you for helping me see what was around the several different corners - and accelerating progress on critical Certified relaunch priorities.\n\n2#Teamwork Central|I wanted to take the time to thank all of you for your hard work and dedication over these past few months as we‚Äôve worked toward this massive expansion of our old Customer Center and ultimately unveiling the new Customer Central to all customers. You were all integral in this project, and I cannot thank you enough. Whether you were developing the content, creating the massive number of images throughout the site, mapping the site layout, reviewing on a daily basis, integrating our access codes in Salesforce, assisting in a complete URL update, coordinating a massive email campaign, or helping me with one of my million requests, this was truly a team effort. Hopefully you can all take a moment to reflect on what a massive accomplishment this is. Thank you all again!\n\n3#Champion of Culture, Connection and GSD|Jill! You are leading our Marketing Social Committee with passion, thoughtfulness and inclusion. You keep us engaged and focused on our shared vision of strengthening connections between our colleagues AND on top of your day job, which you masterfully execute every single day, you GET sh*t DONE for the social committee! Couldn't be a better leader in Marketing to be at the helm of our efforts. On behalf of all of us, I wanted to acknowledge and thank you for your commitment to making us a stronger team. You are amazing in so many ways and we are grateful for you.\n\n4#It's sure good to have \"Friends\"!|Team - Thank you for a wonderful Marketing and \"Customer Strategy Friends\" all hands today. Our existing customers are the best source of growth and play a critical role in helping us secure new business as well. It was a superior All Hands today where we were able to unpack and share insights around how we go to market across the business. Jill and Chase, thank you for leading the charge to stand this up. Chris, appreciate the strategic overview of your entire organization. Eileen and Dave, thank you for the deep dives into your customer base, and providing an outlook around Marketing's role in accounts growth. Lee, Mark, and Nicole, thank you for being the backbone of great execution for the webinar! With gratitude, -C\n\n5#Spreading the Conversations Love|I really appreciated you asking for the Conversations materials I'm sharing with new hires, so you can reinforce with your entire team, and I also LOVED that you're also sharing with other managers in your group. Imagine that ripple effect, just from a simple onboarding training!  From our \"meet and greet\" when I first started, you've been so kind to offer answers to questions and collaboration - thank you!\n\n6#Workhuman Live Follow Up Strategies|What would I even do without the two of you?  Thank you both for meeting to strategize the follow up plans for Workhuman Live with me.  I'm in the midst of still working on acquisition for the event - and follow up loomed over me like a dark cloud.  By working together, we were able to strategize next steps for the follow up that are manageable and the right thing to do for the business.  I so appreciate you both jumping in to help, as you always do.  Thank you.  A thousand times, thank you.\n\n7#Cultivating Customer Growth|Jill, Abby, Chase - Great progress this week! I appreciate how you‚Äôve lined up behind the porfolio‚Äôs goals and algined to supporting differentiated plans for growth. Jill - exciting to see the Team Awards demand process be pursued as well as the new approach to email marketing. Chase and Abby - awesome to see the individualized SCD plans come together as well as the Executive Forum plan advance. Growing and retaining our existing customers is such a large aspect of our growth. Thank you for all you are doing here! With gratitude, -C\n\n8#Leading the charge|Thank you Jill for truly leading the way on our vendor shift away from Sendoso to ANYTHING ELSE. From researching vendors, to coordinating demos, to sending meeting notes and recordings - you've done SO much. More importantly, you've been so careful to ensure everyone feels heard and seen and has had a seat at the table to ask questions and ensure that whatever solution we move forward with is one that works for all parties involved THANK YOU for being such a rock star advocate for us all!\n\n9#Executive Forum Book Mailer|Thank you all for the incredible work you have done for the success of the WHL Executive Book Mailer. This was one of my first (almost) solo projects at WH and I say almost because of all the help and answers to questions you provided. There was plenty of speedbumps on this, but we managed it and it came out looking awesome! Thank you all again for the help on this project! I‚Äôm hoping for great results from this.\n\n10#Plan the work. Work the plan.|Jill, Chase - what a fantastic week of progress this week! I think we are well on our way to aligning with portfolio leaders on plans to drive increase account and contacts engagements against the end goals of segment specific plans and increased billings growth! Onward! -C\n\n11#Leading and Role Modeling Our Values|Jill - congrats on 