ch ELT Update Contributions|That's a wrap for March. Team - our weekly Marketing updates for the ELT are getting better and better. Thank you for helping to showcase all the fine work, progress and RESULTS that are happening across the department. I realize we can be a bit \"deck happy\" around here, and I'm guessing you've probably even rolled your eyes a time or two when you see me coming every week, but I couldn't do what I do without YOUR contributions. Thanks again!\n\n15#Spotlight Success|Team ‚Äì what a massive win on today‚Äôs Workhuman Spotlight event!  It was an absolute thrill to watch it.  Thank you for the ingenuity and reimagination that went in to concepting and planning this new ‚Äòtalk show edition‚Äô format, and for all of the detailed execution that went into todays broadcast.  You all nailed it!  From audience acquisition, to garnering fantastic talent for the show, to the ‚Äòon the Streets of New York‚Äô segment which I thought was a hit, to the carefully constructed questions and content to highlight the many opportunities and challenges facing HR today, not to mention the flawless streaming, it all came together extremely well and showcased our natural place as thought leaders and drivers of this important ‚Äòfuture of work‚Äô conversation.  Steve ‚Äì you handled the job of navigating the conversations with Laurie, Steve and yes, even the unscripted Gary Vaynershuk too, like an absolute pro.  I‚Äôm excited about the demand this event will undoubtedly drive in the final weeks of Workhuman Live Atlanta registration, and equally as optimistic about our prospects for more Spotlight events and format testing in the future.   Thank you to this cross-functional team of trailblazers and innovators, and congratulations on a fantastic event!\n\n16#Spreading appreciation|Jill - thank you for your ongoing support! Each week I send out the recap of the WH blog posts, and most weeks I am lucky to find a reply from you in my inbox. Whether it's a comment on a specific piece or just a quick thank you, it always puts a smile on my face. It's great to know you are benefiting from the content and I hope others are too. Thank you for your positivity and commitment to WH's success ü•≥ ü§©\n\n17#The perfect partners|Allison and Jill, I can't thank you enough for your early collaboration on the rollout of Customer Central. From our initial discussion, I knew we were in good hands and through our early planning and creation of the project brief that feeling has only solidified. I am grateful your expertise in communicating with customers, activating the appropriate channels, and campaign planning, knowing the right timing and resources to pull in. And on top of that, you are always just a pleasure to meet and talk with. Thank you for your strong collaboration to deliver a top-notch customer-centric experience and solution for me and my team as well as our customers.\n\n18#Quite an undertaking‚Ä¶|Who‚Äôs that taking on the challenge to go to RFP with a new vendor to replace Sendoso? JILL! Quite an undertaking on top of your day job, but I appreciate how thorough you‚Äôve been throughout this process thus far. Bringing the right people into presentations from Alyce and PFL, following up with our questions and creating a space to deliver feedback. You‚Äôre working on preparing the massive shift that will need to take place when we do make the switch. This affects more than just Marketing and the U.S. Wonderful job making sure everything is considered with respect to branding, experience, global aspects, and so much more. I hope the next vendor of choice truly puts the work in to prioritize Workhuman and create the best user and customer experience. With your lead, i‚Äôm sure this will happen. Thank you, Jill!\n\n19#Always thinking of the team|Jill, thank you for organizing the watch party of Spotlight today, it was great for the team to watch it together and will inspire them even more to get their customers to attend.  I really appreciate that our customer interactions and how best to support our team, myself included is always to the front of your mind! I also appreciate the discussion today on the exec comp codes and the follow up.  I value you, Jill and the impact that you make on all that we do, thank you for being a wonderful partner in all that CS is doing and making it enjoyable along the way with your humour (badly needed at times!)\n\n20#Great Debriefs|Team, really appreciate the series of meetings we had in the last few weeks to look at results, what went well and areas of opportunity moving forward for three important Customer initiatives. A special shoutout to Allison, Jaclyn, Mark, Jill and Kristen for leading the presentations and fruitful discussion, but everyone in this group contributed with valuable insights and suggestions that will no doubt pave the way to even more efficient and effective future campaigns. Thank you all!\n\n21#Queen of LinkedIn Sourcing|Just wanted to give you a HUGE shoutout to you, for not only jumping right in to LinkedIn sourcing but for directly identifying and reaching out to the candidate we went on to hire! I cannot thank you enough for all of your support in the recruiting process - this role was filled in what feels like record time thanks to you! THANK YOU!!!!\n\n22#When friends bring friends!|Team - thank you for an OUTSTANDING Marketing and HX Friends all hands today! Sarah, Tyler, Stuart, and David - thank you for the wide ranging strategy board overview showcasing all the initiatives HX is leading to drive retention, career mobility, and a more human experience as our ways of working continue to unfold. Jill - thank you for taking our culture and engagement work to the next level to explore new ways to sustain and create moments of connection that matter. And Lee and Mark - another outstanding and well prepared set of panel Q&As and webinar tech magic. I appreciate all that goes into a successful all hands like today, and wanted to celebrate this group's preparedness and terrific content tailored for Marketing. With gratitude, -C\n\n23#I called in the reinforcements|Thank you so much to both of you for ALL of your support when it comes to working with Sendoso. I cannot tell you how much I appreciate it. It has been a challenge for me and to know I have backup feels incredibly good. Thanks for pushing on them and having my back when it comes to the issues I've been facing. I know you're both incredibly busy and yet you still take the time to help and I've learned a lot from you both in the process. You've been fantastic partners throughout.\n\n24#Speaking of Employee Appreciation Day‚Ä¶.|Thank you to this group of humans who contributed to the success of the Human Engagement piece of the Employee Appreciation Day campaign. Jill and Allison, thank you for involving HE in this campaign and for helping to communicate the details internally. Sophia, thank you for incorporating the campaign details in the Feb release highlights. Jack, thank you for helping us determine the best way to design the experiment. Alan and Simone, thank you for your help with the guide design and ensuring the right users receive it. And thank you, Alan, for gathering early data to show the impact of the first email. Phil, thank you for helping me troubleshoot the problems we ran into with the list, and for being a second set of eyes on the workflow and segment changes I needed to make mid-campaign. Allyson, thank you for building the templates and updating them with my many changes. Danielle, Jose, Meghan, and Dave, thank you for sharing client feedback ‚Äì we learned a lot from this campaign. Kevin and Martina, thank you for your support and guidance throughout. And Happy Employee Appreciation Day to you all!\n\n25#Employee Appreciation Day Paid Search|Kudos to this team who built our first-ever Employee Appreciation Day paid search campaign. You didn't have to do it. Many other EAD efforts were planned. It was difficult to get Customer lists uploaded and matched to remarketing lists to enable the sophisticated targeting of Customers searching in Google! You didn't have to have an experiment for Prospects, but one was setup to enable testing between the Guide and the Report. So excited to see how this innovation pays off as we head into EAD next week!\n\n26#LinkedIn Sourcing Rockstar|HUGE shoutout to you, Jill for jumping in to LinkedIn Recruiter to help the hiring process for Mark's backfill! The market is CRAZY right now and when candidates receive a message directly from the hiring manager, it has such a positive impact.  Thank you for being such a great partner in the recruiting process!\n\n27#Lending a helping hand|Jill, thank you for all your support over the recent weeks around Exec Forum.  You stepped in and helped bring the site together, provide copy direction and insight, and get us into a good place to bring it to market.  I know it‚Äôs outside of your scope, but as usual you willingly raised your hand, offering the help and support.  Thank you for always being such a great teammate.\n\n28#Growing our Talent!|Hi Jill - I wanted to recognize your terrific support of Mark in his promotion to Sr Manager, ABM. It is a mark of a great people leader when they grow members of their team to the next level, and also to have the broad organizational perspective, to support their careers in the bigger context of opportunities company-wide. Thank you for supporting our goals around employee mobility and your advocacy of Mark specifically! Well done! -C\n\n29#Collaboration for the win|Team, thank you all for your hard work and dedication towards finalizing all three spark articles for the month of February. With established deadlines to meet and several rounds of revisions (along with all other projects you're involved with), each one of you has helped push this content along to its next stage swiftly and efficiently. I truly value everyone's commitment to providing thought-provoking, customer-curate content for our customers to enjoy ‚Äì thanks again!\n\n30#The momentum continues!|Thank you for attending our second marketing analytics office hours. We had another great session with even more of the team in attendance. As we make it through the measurement matrix it's exciting to see our questions evolve and the implications of how we measure our work continue to become more clear. Thank you for showing up, staying invested and bringing your collective expertise to contribute to the success of marketing analytics.Go team!\n\n31#Marketing Analytics Office Hours | Go team!|Team, thank you for taking time to attend marketing analytics office hours. The rich discussion, commitment to clarification and thoughtful feedback helps the analytics team support this team with much more effectiveness. Thank you for your commitment to rethinking, approaching each other with curiosity and being partners in addressing key questions that arise. Looking forward to all we'll do with analytics in 2022. Go team!\n\n32#|Whew! Jumping back in to help PM the Customer Marketing team this week reminded me how many moving pieces there are, how thoughtful and strategic we are with our customers, and what a great team we have steering the ship! Appreciate your patience as we work on ramping up our new PM, Piper. It‚Äôs not always easy jumping into something right in the middle, but you‚Äôve all been understanding and flexible when needed working together to meet all the deadlines fiercely approaching, one after another! On behalf of Piper and I, thank you for helping us through an important week getting to know each other better and learning some of the fundamentals of customer growth and strategic marketing.\n\n33#Yay for new team members!|THANK YOU to this whole crew for your roles in bringing Lauren to our team! Kate - I can't thank you enough for referring Lauren! I'm sure you sold her on Workhuman before she even applied, and you did a fantastic job! She even said this was her \"dream company.\" Thank you for brining your dear friend into our WH Family. Daniella - thank you for all of your efforts during the recruitment process. You helped me and Lauren navigate the interesting situation that came up when she applied for one of our roles, but then we said \"Hey, let's see if she'd be up for this other role instead!\" Luckily she was, and it seems like a perfect fit! It's been a pleasure and a breeze working with you, and I'm excited to be working with you on the next new team member, too. Melanie, Brenda, Jill, and Kerri - thank you for your thoughtful questions and insights during the interview process. Each of you pulled different things out of her which made for a robust and thorough feedback session. Thank you all for helping get Lauren on board!\n\n34#Spreading holiday cheer!|Jill, wanted to thank you for coordinating a holiday trivia and beer tasting!  You always go above and beyond to find creative ways to bring the team together and this gathering was no exception. This virtual event was full of laughs and learnings - both from the trivia (note to self: brush up on my skills for next year!) and the team. I learned important things like Kelsey's go to trivia/wifi network name is Egg Salad (with no real explanation...), Chase's secret power is trivia, Kristen is highly competitive, Anthony Hawkins did the voice over in How the Grinch Stole Christmas and so much more. What a fun way to end the year! Thanks again!\n\n35#Sendoso Superstar|Jill, I wanted to take the time to genuinely thank you for all of your help and commitment towards ensuring all of Sendoso packages are delivered timely & efficiently. You're always the first one to offer assistance and dig in / straighten things out when a question comes up. Thank you for always being a team player and for taking the lead when necessary!!\n\n36#Snowball effect of gratitude|Jill and Meghan owned this year‚Äôs Workhuman holiday card. They had a vision to create a beautiful social recognition experience for both customers and future customers revealing how recognition moments can snowball into something more meaningful through our connections, partnerships and gratitude. Alana, Katie, Liu, Cullen and Owen collaborated on the animation and found a way to bring it to life, together. We had some hurdles along the way, but in the end made the message and graphics better and stronger! Thank you for all the time and energy you put into this project to get it just right! And Rachel, thank you for swooping in at the end to build everything quickly in order to hit our deadlines and work with our partners to ensure they have everything they need. I am snow thankful for each of you!\n\n37#There is a Superhero in all of us|Blown away again by his team's commitment to dropping everything to come together and use their collective talents to drive the business. Here's to all of you in celebration of teamwork!  When it matters most, we step up, rally the troops, and march right into the battle headfirst. Yesterday was another great example of what happens when you bring great minds together, the sparks fly, the ideas flow and suddenly we have a solution. There is a Superhero in all of us, we just have to put on the cape. Cheers to the team!\n\n38#Successful Giving Tuesday Outreach|On Giving Tuesday, we successfully deployed an email to 115k end-users, across 130 clients, spreading the message of recognition and giving back. As a result, 6,200 users were driven to their recognition programs that might not have logged in otherwise. Additional data is still be gathered, and I‚Äôm sure we will see more fantastic results from this effort. Kevin, thank you for bringing Human Engagement into this initiative. It was a great opportunity to promote the importance of recognition and raise awareness of charity gift card options in the Store. Erin, thank you for securing the list of clients. Without your efforts, we could not have reached so many end-users. Phil, thank you for helping to collect all the user data, and for helping to ensure we reached the full intended audience. Jill, thank you for keeping the customers in mind and doing a sanity check on audience selection with me ‚Äì it‚Äôs so important to ensure we‚Äôre aligned in our efforts and doing what‚Äôs right by our customers.\n\n39#Growth Advocate|Jill - I wanted to take a moment and acknowledge the important aspects of people leadership you demonstrated in a meeting this week about the professional growth of employees on your team. People leadership involves a wide ranging set of responsibilities - growth, motivation, coaching, counsel, leading with empathy, and respectful challenge. I appreciate your ability to check all of those boxes in your plans for career development of people on your team. This showed up as you advocating for a particular high potential employee this week. Amidst the Great Resignation, building bench and retaining talent matters now more than ever. Thank you for modeling this important leadership behavior. With gratitude, -C\n\n40#Thankful for You|This is the time of year where everyone is rushing toward the 'finish line'--literally pushing themselves and each other toward another year of record breaking performance. It's the crush of renewal season, always a bit stressful and uncertain until the deals are done. Thank you for hanging in there for each other and acting with integrity and professionalism. I'm so thankful to work with each of you! Wishing you a beautiful long weekend with your family and friends. On to December! Gobble Gobble!\n\n41#Analytics Rockstars|Team, thanks so much for the quick turnaround on data and thoughtful dialogue around our customer marketing programs! It felt like a great example of how powerful cross-department collaborative efforts can be. So thanks again for all your hard work we really appreciate it!\n\n42#Holiday Greetings Partnership|Team ‚Äì thanks for looping me into the 2021 holiday greetings and Sendoso sends. Kelsey and Evan ‚Äì I appreciate the context and clarity you provided on setting up Sendoso touches as well as the supporting PowerPoint with details. Taylor ‚Äì thank you for assisting me with prospect bundle creation and for reviewing the communications. Jill ‚Äì thank you for continuing to keep me informed and looping me into projects for visibility. I really appreciate your support. Looking forward to collaborating on future initiatives!\n\n43#Customer Marketing Magic|Jill ‚Äì Another long overdue callout for everything you do! Over the past few months, you‚Äôve continued to be the worlds best partner. You‚Äôre help in managing on going customer contact work, Salesforce cleanup, marketing tech, IN ADDITION to all the marketing programs established over the past two years is nothing short of astounding. You are a rock in the customer strategy team and I cannot thank you enough!\n\n44#Banding together|I wanted to take a minute to thank you all for the recent ‚Äúcoming together‚Äù of our 2022 plans. We‚Äôve been working together more closely these past few weeks than I think we ever have before. It‚Äôs been great to get better perspective on the customer programs, to hear everyone's perspectives on what‚Äôs possible (and how we can get there), and to identify synergies and areas of opportunity that we may not have explored or discussed in the past. I‚Äôm grateful to work with such talented, open-minded and supportive people. And I can‚Äôt wait to see how our plans come to life, and together in January!\n\n45#Scenario Planning Sesh #1 was what I'd call a Win|My head is spinning from all the inspired thinking in today's planning meeting. Thank you for sharing your Plans on a Page <or is it 'Plan on a Pages?!'> with the broader team. Thank you for deep diving into some of our Marketing priorities to identify integration points, gaps, opportunities for testing, and more. It was awesome to see different people gather to collaborate cross-functionally and spend time thinking about the \"what if sh....scenarios.\" And lastly, thank you for being good sports about the ice breakers questions. From Buzz Lightyear to time machine travel, childhood crushes  and early retirement dreams, I learned a lot of new things about each of you today!  And yet, I am sure you all agree that it felt like we barely scratched the surface in our three hours today. Not to worry! This is the starting point and I have a good feeling that this was just the first of many Scenario Planning sessions to come. So strap in and look forward to next steps AND the next invite. I am excited to work together to ensure we are set up to deliver business results, feel proud of our work, and have some fun along the way.\n\n46#Taking a page right out of the Teamwork Playbook|...as in \"Marketing Plan on a Page\" page! Thank you, Jess for jumping right in to design the template for our Marketing Plan on a Page and thank you Jen and Jill for helping me test it for usability!  Things are coming together! Let's GOOOO!\n\n47#The goal is progress, not perfection!|‚ÄúFirst steps are always the hardest but until they are taken the notion of progress remains just a notion and not an achievement‚Äù ‚Äî Through a time of transition, new planning processes and forecasts, and current executional needs this team has been exceptional. You‚Äôve come together, forced needed changes, asked the right questions, and most importantly you‚Äôve done it as a team. Thank you for leading by example, overcoming the daily challenges, and for accepting new perspectives and approaches.   You are building our game plans now so we can all enter the stadium with confidence together next year.   Remember, The goal is progress, not perfection\n\n48#You're Nailing it with Customer Comms Toolkits!|On our recent Customer Experience Survey, Dawn from Tennant had a wonderful, unsolicited callout stating:  \"I really like the toolkits to support communications in the company. They have been very useful!\" Honestly, getting any comments back from customers is sometimes like pulling teeth, especially praise, so the fact that this long-standing customer took the time to highlight this deserves a shout-out from the rooftop! To the incredible team behind these toolkits:  Congratulations and THANK YOU!  You are creating moments that matter and delivering the Workhuman experience with every connection!\n\n49#Rethinking in Action|Jill, this is long overdue and entirely necessary! Over the past six months you have led some major rethinking regarding our use of technology in customer marketing. From asking honest questions to managing vendor CSMs and keeping internal contributors moving, you have juggled a lot and also helped us move the right things forward. In this process I have appreciated your leadership, focus on realistic expectations and drive to implement solutions that work cross functionally. Thank you for leading us towards interesting conversations and unified implementation!\n\n50#Spark Customer Innovation Center|Allison, Evan, and Jill - What an amazing journey we have been on together! After nearly a year of webinars and two months of content creation and planning, we are on the cusp of launching the Spark Customer Inspiration Center for all Workhuman customers. This new site will be a showcase of inspirational customer content - including both upcoming and past webinars, as well as written articles to engage customers on various topics. We have already gained so much traction and engagement through the webinars...I can't wait to see how the articles help us reach even more customers and personas. All of your amazing work from event promotion to editing and tracking to working with the Creative team on the page design has resulted in something truly magical. It has been a joy working with each of you and I can't thank you enough for bringing your amazing talents, positivity, and determination to the table throughout this entire process. You should each be so proud of this incredible accomplishment! Thank you!\n\n51#Best partner ever!|Jill- this award is LONG overdue! I have to thank you for your ongoing partnership every single day. You give everything your all, regardless of what you are working on, and always deliver! Just recently, I brought to you a situation where we had a customer who had several comp passes to WH Live San Antonio built in their contract, who wanted to come next year, but didnt have budget, and was wondering if we would still offer the comps for her and her boss. I had no idea where to take this, but knew I needed a quick turnaround given the circumstances. I brought it to you, and literally by the next day, you had the passes for me‚Ä¶AND you even took it a step further to figure out what other customers are in the same boat. By the next day, you came back with what other customers were impacted and had their passes ready to go, to deliver proactively which will no doubt drive up our registrations. This is just one of many examples of why you are the best partner ever! I just want you to know, on behalf of all of Customer Success, we SO appreciate everything that you do to support our teams and our customers- from the toolkits, to driving forward and communicating what marketing efforts are underway, to creating custom marketing campaigns when we need details on specific customers, to just always bringing a warm smile to our calls and the best jokes! Thank you Jill!! P.S. if I had design skills, I absolutely would have replaced superwomen‚Äôs face with yours for the image used in this award! :-)\n\n52#Behind the scenes leadership for WGD|Jill - thank you for recommending we give Allison time today to share the results of the World Gratitude Day program with the Customer Marketing team. The bar has been raised - once again! And I have no doubt that you will continue to inspire others and then shine a light on them so we can all learn from successes and sometimes even failures because that's how we grow. Clearly, in this particular case - it was nothing but success for the 2021 World Gratitude Day customer marketing program. I want you to know we are grateful for your unwavering support and leadership.\n\n53#Feeling inspired!|Team - I wanted to thank you for all your collaboration and hard work on reimagining the team awards landing page.  Revamping this landing page has been no easy task but this team came together to brainstorm ideas, rethink the design and flow, tweak messaging and the output shows! The new page (even in wireframe form!) really brings team awards to life in an inspiring, new way. We've received positive feedback across the board on the new direction of the page from stakeholders. Thank you again for all your work on this page!  I'm excited to see it come to life.\n\n54#You're my Jedi Master|Oh wise and powerful Jill.  Thank you so much for taking time out of your hectic schedule to provide me guidance this week when I was in a bit of a pickle.  I can't tell you how much I appreciated being able to reach out and get your opinion on a challenging situation.  It wasn't your responsibility at all, but it was reassuring to chat things through with you and come up with a perfect solutions.  Thanks for always being a great colleague and friend!\n\n55#Getting those books out!|Jill, thank you so much for your support in moving the Lighthouse book project forward with Sendoso this week. There was no shortage of trials and tribulations ‚Äì lost books, severe delays in shipping, unanswered tickets, the list goes on. I appreciate you raising the issues with our account manager, looping me in and connecting me with her, and for helping to see this through. Jason, thank you for carrying us the last mile by turning on the UK touches and uploading the necessary lists. I really appreciate your willingness to lend a helping hand! Taylor, thank you for setting us up for success while you were away - getting the lists ready, the touches set up, and the handoff ready. I know there was a lot of behind-the-scenes work that you did, and it hasn't gone unnoticed. Thank goodness the prospects and customers who receive the books will have no idea of the hoops we had to jump through. Thank you all!\n\n56#And thats a wrap!|Thank you for bringing your brilliance, remarkable talents, expertise, creativity, innovative thinking, and skills to drive the successful execution of the Spotlight broadcast and WHLive registration launch.  The work for these projects starts months in advance and continues for weeks after we go live. Over the last several months, there were endless moments of comradery, collaboration, and a continuous drive to raise the bar.    The road was challenging, but despite the obstacles, YOU DID IT!  You delivered a fabulous production and flawless launch.   Your passion is contagious. Congratulations and celebrate the moment!!\n\n57#Fantastic Follow Up|Jill and Laura - thank you, thank you, thank you for all of your work on follow up programs for Spotlight.  Thanks to you, our team had the bandwidth to focus on preparing for and launching Workhuman Live 2022 promotions.  You are both always amazing partners to the events team, but the incremental effort to prioritize Spotlight amid many other priorities does not go unnoticed.  Thank you for your partnership, collaboration and teamwork.\n\n58#Truly grateful for your leadership and guidance|Jill, thank you SO much for all you do! This last month has been incredibly hectic yet you've exemplified (yet again) what ideal leadership looks like. In preparation for my paternity we've come across full workloads, tight timelines and still thrived to get ahead, and stay ahead! You have guided me to stay incredibly focused and prioritize which allowed me to stay flexible to accommodate juggling outside appointments with ease. THANK YOU!!\n\n59#Sparking Up Something Good!!|Allison, Erin and Jill, I wanted to thank all three of you for your help in positioning the spark series for absolute success! With great ideas come new processes and new ways of working, and I couldn't be happier to have passed off this first round of content on time and with little to no hiccups along the way. Each of you took the time to review and approve each piece, while adapting to an entirely new process for collaboration. While we still have a little way to go before everything is live, I'm so excited to see this vision come to fruition and I'm so so grateful for everyone's hard work!\n\n60#Customer collaboration|Jill, I just wanted to send a private message saying what a pleasure it is collaborating with you on all things customer marketing.  We just finished recording the monthly newsletter and, as always, you made it easy and fun.  Whenever we have new ideas on things like building a stable of guest presenters you jump on the ideas and action them every time.  (And you're one of the few people I trust to host the Customer Strategy huddles).  Working with you is always a pleasure.  Thanks for being you!\n\n61#Very important!|Jill - thank you for taking initiative to consolidate the cross-section of opportunities in our CRM and SFDC tools that will make us more effective at growing profitable sales. Many of these fall outside of core marketing and your leadership is appreciated. -C\n\n62#Sometimes, it takes a village|Team, I wanted to take a minute to thank you all for your support on our recent webinar promotions for the Lighthouse Effect webinar. Carrie, you did an amazing job weaving the ‚Äúmood‚Äù of the World Gratitude Day brand creative into the promotional assets for this program. And you knocked the new social ad formats out of the park. Rachel, you did a phenomenal job on the email ‚Äì building it in a super timely fashion with a keen eye for detail. Anthony, thank you for all your fancy footwork on the landing page for book requests. You got the page up faster than I could blink and did a stellar job at improvising when/where needed. Olivia, thank you for getting the promotions out the door and into market in such a timely manner. Jess, as always, you did an incredible job with the key takeaways doc - something that is extremely useful and appreciated by everyone, including the Sales team. Rachael, you managed the heck out of this program; keeping many balls in the air at once, reviewing and approving countless documents, following up in a timely fashion with all stakeholders, and thinking of every minor detail possible. Jill, Jason, and Taylor ‚Äì thanks for all the support on the book order and with Sendoso. As a Sendoso rookie, I really appreciate the insights and knowledge that you all shared, and the assistance with managing the whole Sendoso program. Sometimes, it really does take a village! And in the end, this was our 2nd largest webinar by volume ever! Thanks for making it possible.\n\n63#Leveling Up Our Customer Game|Rich, thanks so much for taking the time to walk the team through a customer launch. It was really eye-opening to see the launch process and how an initial kick-off works. I love that the team was so focused and asked great questions. Looking forward to my continued education on this process!\n\n64#Gratitude for your FIRE!|To this incredible team of pros, I hope you are dancing alongside me (virtually) to our theme song! You are the Fire in the band! How lucky are we all to work together and make work for millions of people centered in gratitude?! I'm grateful for each of you every day and inspired by your passion, drive, and leadership. Dance a little, sing a little, and feel celebrated---Never was a cloudy day!\n\n65#Helping Hands!|Every once in a while you hit one of those weeks that is just really hard, but when you have people that you work with who step up and help without skipping a beat, it makes it so much easier to navigate. Jill and Mark, first it has been so great working closely with you lately. I am always energized by our conversations and learn so much from all of your knowledge and expertise. Secondly, I can not thank you enough for how supportive you have been, not just this past week, but in general. Thank you for being the definition of humans, working human!!\n\n66#K-P-I Oh My!|Team - outstanding job developing, vetting, socializing, and finalizing a set of Existing Customer marketing accountability metrics that align with the overall CS shared goals of growth. Superior work and great cross-functional partnership between Analytics, Marketing, and the CS business teams demonstrated here. I appreciate this team setting and achieving a goal to accomplish this work within Q3. With gratitude, -C\n\n67#Winner, Winner, Chicken Dinner|Team - Congratulations on all of your hard work with Workhuman's submission to the 2021 HRO Today's Baker's Dozen Award program.  Because of you, Workhuman has claimed the #1 spot!!!   You should feel very proud of your work.  As the #1 Recognition vendor on the planet, we are able to launch a global brand campaign and acquisition campaign to educate HR leaders and practitioners about the urgent importance of making work more human.  Take a bow. You earned it.\n\n68#Product Enablement|Ladies!  Thank you for managing the product speaker segments for Spotlight - and providing all the details necessary to share with the Sales and Customer Success teams prior to launch.  We are always striving to provide the teams enough information about our events during the promotional period - and this can be challenging because we are typically building the content while promoting it.  Because of your efforts, we are able to provide a substantial preview of what to expect in the broadcast before we even launch - and that will certainly help as the teams do outreach to generate registrations.  I'll partner with you both any time!\n\n69#Customer Marketing <3|Jill, this week you set up a customer marketing sharing session with another team in the customer marketing world. In this session, we got to see how others are doing customer marketing at their company, talk to those in similar roles to us, share ideas, ask questions and more. It was so great to connect with other customer marketers.  I left this session feeling inspired and excited about all the things that are possible. I don't know how you make the time to do all the things you do for us but it is greatly appreciated. Thank for setting this sharing session up and for everything you do for our team!\n\n70#World's best pinch hitter|Jill, thank you SO much for pinch hitting for me while I was on vacation last week. You didn't just cover me, you exemplified yet again what an amazing leader you are and went well above and beyond. From coming back to perfect updates and recaps, to ensuring I really do unplug and spend the time with my family I literally can't thank you enough!!\n\n71#Respect for Quality QBRs!|With the pace of business and everything on our plates, it's easy to want to just keep your head down and march forward...However, it's important to stop, look back and evaluate the past. With the right mindset, the past offers lessons that can influence the future - helping us work smarter, make better marketing investment, strengthen our process, refine our messaging/creative and ultimately shape what we will test and optimize next. We wrap the 2Q'QBR up on Monday and I wanted to say THANK YOU to each of you for the time and effort you put into documenting and sharing key insights from your respective areas of marketing expertise. QBRs are an important part of the planning cycle and I am grateful for your commitment to them.\n\n72#Customer Newsletters delivered seamlessly|Jill and Allison, thank you so much for your partnership and dedication to quality as we put together these monthly customer newsletter videos.  You have worked hard to get the process refined to the point where we can deliver great insights in a sustainable way and your effort has not gone unnoticed.  You have gone out of your way on many occasions to make it easier on me personally as well.  It takes a real commitment to quality and customers to deliver something like this time and time again.  I just wanted you to know that it is wonderful to partner with you on it.\n\n73#Signed, sealed and delivered|I have lost track of the weeks we've spent working on the taxonomy that will support insights coming from 6sense, and I know there would have been many more weeks without this team. Thank you all for coming together to finalize, review, finalize, review, finalize, review and finalize the taxonomy for 6sense. Going through rows of data, building out taxonomy architecture and making it make business sense is not an easy task. And doing that along with your business as usual commitments is an even trickier tasks. Thank you team for making the time, reviewing the information and most of all investing in this effort. Looking forward to the impact that our work will have. Go team!\n\n74#The Mighty Growth Pod|Allison, Mark and Jill, thank you all so much for your help over the past week and a half! Allison - I seriously cannot thank you enough for the level of detail you provided me with in your pto handoff doc. You really took organization to the max here, allowing me to work on all the things with comfort and ease while you were on vacation! Mark - thank you for stepping in and helping me out with any and all questions / rogue issues that popped up while Allison was on pto. You're always a team player & it really means a lot! Jill - I appreciate you stepping in and helping me navigate these projects over the past few days. Whether it be providing approvals or filling in the missing details, your guidance here has been key to keeping up with the fast pace of these projects!\n\n75#Working Human Champions Unite!|I wanted to express my gratitude to this fine team of colleagues who have come together to share ideas, express concerns and TAKE ACTION to help shape the human experience and culture for our Marketing team. Your commitment goes way back to last fall when we formed the original Pulse Survey Groups but we reinvented ourselves about a month ago and decided there is strength in numbers. When you share a common goal and vision, it might make sense to join forces. And, wow...were we spot on. I love the collaboration and get giddy when hearing and seeing the larger group feed off each other's ideas. This group championed the DiSC workshop as our first official all hands L&D opportunity. This group helped reimagine the town hall as a platform to showcase the strong work and diverse voices across all of Marketing. This group is thinking ahead to what the next phase of work, when we step away from our Zoom calls and return to the office in some form or fashion, means for our newest marketers and everyone else that survived the last year+! This group is thoughtfully pulling together strategies to help foster the human connections that will inevitably make our team stronger and our work even better. It's a side hustle when we are all hustled out most days, but it matters and I genuinely appreciate your investment. We've only scratched the surface, but after receiving positive feedback on yesterday's town hall and coming off of a lively planning call with many of you earlier today regarding our next couple of initiatives, I am feeling optimistic about the journey we've chosen to take together. #btpftp THANK YOU for your commitment to me, to each other, to all of Marketing, and to working human!\n\n76#2H Global Marketing Plans|Team, I just wanted to thank everyone for their hard work and input on our 2H 2021 global marketing plans. I really appreciated all the thoughtful feedback and help along the way, very excited to get these into action!\n\n77#Interviewing Pros!|Thank you so much to this team for dedicating a whole morning to becoming MASTER interviewers! This was a huge time commitment, and I really appreciate that you spent your morning learning all about how to effectively interview at Workhuman. You were all so engaged throughout the session - asking questions and sharing your insights. Not to mention you were SO gracious with me when we had a couple of little hiccups (so many types of unconscious bias to define....and a whiny dog who refused to not go out). This was such an enjoyable session, and it was clear from your participation that you all really took it seriously and truly care about the quality of your interviews and hiring decisions. Thank you so much for taking this step in helping us to continue to hire the BEST talent at Workhuman!\n\n78#Keeping us heading the right direction|Thank you so much for all the help in the world of growth initiatives. The work you two have put into helping us move the ball forward on everything from lead-gen to Salesforce trainings has indispensable. We have a million things going on, somehow you two consistently make sure we are headed in the right direction. I cannot express enough how grateful I am to be on a team with you two! Great things are on the horizon!\n\n79#Of course you can!!|Jill, thank you for being a wonderful partner to Customer Success. This is just one example of the many requests that you take on & respond with imagination, collaboration & always such customer focus. I admire how positively you respond & how thoughtful you are in providing a solution, feedback or simply being open to a conversation. This slide is a great talking point during reviews, a good summary for those who would like to learn more or an education piece for a new PM, I love the detail & the links to learn more. We really value you & all that you do, great job!\n\n80#WHLO Retro|Thank you for completing the WHLO survey within the allotted timeframe. Your feedback is important to help drive improvements in how we work on future events. I appreciate your time and input. Your voice has been heard. Cheers!\n\n81#Pioneering the Human Workplace|Thank you all for your months-long efforts in creating Workhuman Live Online. Together, you showcased the importance, impact, and transformative power of putting humans at the center of the workplace.    Doing that took the cooperation of teams across Workhuman, including Technology, Product, Workhuman iQ, Sales, Customer Strategy, Customer Service, Finance, Legal, HX, and Marketing. It was a tremendous effort, and in turn, I am immensely proud of what we accomplished.   I know there were difficult moments during the broadcasts, so I want to specifically call out the resolve and focus many of you demonstrated in supporting our customers and prospects with rapid-response access to key content.    While I would say, ‚Äúthat‚Äôs a wrap‚Äù the truth is this is just a beginning‚Äîthe response has been overwhelmingly positive, and I look forward to seeing the impact it has our company‚Äôs growth in the future.   Ultimately, the greatest demonstration of the power of working human is all of you. So again, thank you for the commitment, hard work, and humanity you brought to Workhuman Live Online.    With gratitude, -C\n\n82#Customer moment of surprise and delight|Jill, Eileen and Alice, thank you all for jumping right in with both feet when we wanted to create a moment of surprise and delight for customers attendees at WH Live Online.  All of you brought ideas, action bias and urgency and we were able to quickly turn around a delightful surprise.  I've received a number of appreciative notes in response - including from the executive sponsor at our biggest customer - and your willingness to roll up the sleeves and jump right in was critical in making it happen.  Thank you!\n\n83#There's no stopping you!|Jill, is there anything you won't do for our customers? For WHLO, you drove the creation of an amazing enablement deck for our customer facing teams so they had everything they needed to support our customers pre and post event. Then, when the post event plans needed adjusting, you dove in and got the right people onboard, cleared blockers, developed content