ke a moment to thank this team for coming together so quickly to bring an important DEI resource and landing page to life for our WHLO follow ups in a matter of days. From joining last minute meetings, to hunting down content, organizing chaotic schedules, recording a teaser video, and launching a new landing page - this team came together and made it happen. I think we're even ahead of schedule!  Appreciate everyone jumping in and helping us pull this off.\n\n88#Urgency and teamwork at its finest.|Under tight deadlines you two ALWAYS shine no matter the project. We have several projects with tight timelines running at once and we've been able to not just collaborate, but exceed milestones. Specifically for WHLO follow up, you've turned around revisions, pivoted, and kept the optimal customer experience always top of mind for us all. Jill, you lead us through everything so seamlessly all while challenging us to rethink what's possible to truly bring our marketing to the next level. Allison I can't even count how many times we've hoped on a quick call to work though a road bump, found a solution and ended up making the solution better than it was before there was an issue! I am SO grateful to work with both of you and look forward to future accomplishments, GSD!!!\n\n89#Starting strong|Jill, Chase and Kristen, thank you for taking the time this week to meet with Chris and I to talk about all things Customer Development. The meeting was informative, productive and even a little fun :) Thanks for also setting up a place in Sharepoint with really helpful examples of past work and metrics. I'm super excited for the opportunity to partner and do great things together, big or small.\n\n90#Meet Jill - A Shining Example for All.|Jill - this is long overdue but I wanted to recognize and thank you for consistently being SO GOOD. AT ALL THE THINGS. You never miss a deadline, you are always engaged in the process, in the meeting, in the discussion...whatever it may be - you are 