ndset. Your creativity and internal knowledge are boundless! I could have given this same award and message for so many instances where you've been my rescuer and my \"go-to person\" to help out a customer, most recently with an ask from Air Products to help influence internal stakeholders and drive excitement around DEI efforts. You found and provided to me perfect materials to support the customer's ask. Thank you!\n\n94#Q2 Customer Strategy Team Meeting|Thank you all for making today's Q2 Customer Strategy Meeting a resounding success! (In order of appearance) Jill, Leslie, Jack and Jesse thank you for kicking us off by highlighting three key initiatives for 2021.  And thank you for your leadership on these projects and the clear, concise communication of the purpose and progress in each.  Well done! Alan, Erica, Isha, Meisha-Ann and Yi thank you for bringing the \"candy\"! Your section was filled with amazing insights, thought-provoking commentary and expert analysis.  You truly are pushing the boundaries of the industry forward.  Thank you (again) Jesse  for leading such a talented team of experts. And Dana, thank you for aligning all the logistics, for putting the story pieces together and keeping us all on track.  Well done everyone! Great meeting!\n\n95#A focus on our new humans|Hey Jill, I wanted to take a moment and recognize you for the effort you put in to our new humans. Onboarding can seem so dull and mundane to old hat employees but it's so exciting, fresh and fun to the new humans we're bringing on board our train! Thanks for the extra time and effort you're putting in to help make the presentation great.\n\n96#Departmental Security Review|Hi folks,  Thanks so much for taking part in our first departmental security review as part of our ISO27001 work.   We're looking forwards to using the results of the questionnaire as a way to increase the security alignment across the organization and we really appreciate the time and effort that people took in their responses!   best regards, Dermot\n\n97#All the progress!|Team - exceptional business review today! Great focus on results aligned to our growth goals. Thank you for your focus, hard work, discipline around evaluating performance and opportunties to accelerate further! Keep it up! These are important behaviors. -C\n\n98#THANK YOU FOR THANKING|Thank you all for your video submission for Employee Appreciation Day! While this day provides a wonderful reminder for all of us to reflect on the efforts and innovation that each of our humans bring to the table - we all know that our spirit of recognition and celebration is one that lives on all year long. There is no greater example of this in action than the recent call for video submissions from people leaders for an Employer Brand campaign. When we asked for some videos from people leaders thanking their team members, we were OVERWHELMED with video submissions - much more than we could incorporate into one or two snippet videos!  Your videos will remain live for all your team mates to see (see slack for link). Thank you all so much for taking the time to show your gratitude and enhancing our culture further. Even in this remote world you are all creating moments that matter, so thank you.\n\n99#Employee Appreciation Day - Thank You!|Jill, I wanted to formally thank you for the thoughtful package you sent over for Employee Appreciation Day. Unless I do some online shopping (which has been pretty frequent lately I'll admit), there really aren't many occasions where I find myself getting excited over opening mail anymore. Thank you for going out of your way to bring some fun to the occasion & the hand written note really sweetened the deal by hitting me right in the heart strings!\n\n100#Recognizing bp in a meaningful way|Thank you for taking the time to create congratulate bp on being named 'Best place to work LGBT+ Equality' by the Human Rights Campaign Foundadtion.  This is such an impressive milestone and one that has deep ties to our tenants of workplace rights.  It is amazing to see our customers leading the charge in making work more human.  And, it's even more amazing to watch our impressive group of talented humans come together to celebrate these moments.  Thank you!\n\n101#Employee Appreciation Day - Nailed it!|Jill, thank you for thinking of me when you sent your team gifts for EAD 2021. I don't really have a team, but you ALWAYS go out of your way to make me feel like a part of yours. As an individual contributor, it means so much to me to be invited to your weekly team meetings and included in your ongoing communications. The employee appreciation day gift was a lovely and unexpected surprise. It was perfect in every way. You might know my fashion sense better than my own family and I can't wait to crack open the cider. In big ways and small ways - all day, every day, you consistently fulfill my workplace right and human need TO BELONG. And I know many colleagues would say the same. My cup runneth over and I am grateful for you.\n\n102#Creative discussion partners!|Team, thank you for your participation, creative discussion and investment in our process of defining Marketing KPIs as we envision our plan for development. I was inspired and motivated by your expertise and feedback during our session yesterday. This has truly been a team effort held up by all humans involved! I'm excited to see where our imagination and determination take marketing analytics.\n\n103#Bridging the Gap!!|I'm not a fan of fire drills but they do happen! :-) LOLOL  I feel so blessed to have a team of \"first responders\" that pulled together a story on Certified's journey to help bridge the gap in understanding of where Certified began and where we aspire for it to grow.  Brian at the lead really assembled the right process owners (Brenda/Melanie) along with up to the minute digital insights and customer feedback & marketing analysis (Deb, Jill and Traci).  IN TWO DAYS!!!  TEAMWORK MAKES THE DREAM WORK! Great work Everyone...\n\n104#Health First webinar is ready!|Thank you ALL for helping us pull of the webinar with Health First. From writing an abstract during the holidays and asking the customer for quick approval, we did it. And I thought that was amazing. But then cut forward to having to put the slides, story, content, and marketing together on an accelerated timeline! And you nailed it. I cannot stress enough how much each if you played a part in the successs and bring such a relatable story to our future customers. I am grateful for each of you. I want to thank you for being so open to collaboration, quick turnarounds, and emotional support during a busy time. I think the session was great and can‚Äôt wait for it to air on SHRM next week. I am truly grateful for each of you and the end result.\n\n105#Visibility 2021|It's February 18! We're almost halfway through the quarter! What a whirlwind 2021 has been. Thanks to this team of inspired minds for coming together this week to review detailed individual action plans for our strategic accounts and also coming together to share our biggest opportunities with each other. We all learn and grow so much together and I LOVE IT! Special shout out to our new BFF, Yuri! Thanks so much for kicking us off, inspiring our thinking, introducing us to the best new yogi 2021, and giving us some insight and vision for the future of WHCE. We're so lucky to have you! Thanks to everyone on the team for contributing to our Periscope project and Data Insights project. We've made some real progress on ass kicking and it's 'only' February! I see you!\n\n106#Warmest Welcome Ever!|Thank you so much to the Customer Development team for the warm welcome and support throughout my first week! Each one of you really went out of your way to make me feel comfortable from day one, and I cannot thank you all enough.  Allison - Thank you for guiding me through my first week with kindness and ease. I really appreciate you taking the time to answer any & all questions I've had, scheduling regular sync meetings with me, and offering me the most organized roll-up plan I could've ever hoped for. Talking to you every day has only built up my excitement for this new position even more, and I'm looking forward to teaming up & working with you!  Mark - I really want to thank you for helping my along this week! I've loved having you as my \"Buddy,\" and I truly appreciate you taking the time out of your busy schedule to check-in with me and give me further insight into how the team operates. I'm excited to work with you & learn from you along the way!  Jill - I cannot stress how thrilled I am to be joining your team! From one fellow Frenchie owner to another, I've enjoyed every one of our conversations and I'm excited to hit the ground running once my onboarding is completed. Thank you for explaining the ins & outs of how team collaboration works here at WH & for bettering my understanding of each team's roles!  Kelsey - Sometimes you can just tell when you're going to get along great with someone, & you're a perfect example of that. From day 1, you made it clear that I can always come to you  if I have any questions or need someone to talk to. I truly value how welcoming you've been, and I look forward to hearing many more \"Would You Rather's\" in the future!   Kristen & Melissa - Thank you both for being so welcoming in our team meetings! I'm really looking forward to getting to know both of you better in the coming weeks, and I couldn't be more excited to be the newest addition to our incredible Customer Dev team!\n\n107#Marketer or Marketeer?|No matter which way you market yourself, Amy and I wanted to thank this entire team for the investment over the last few weeks, leading up to today - our first integrated planning offsite of 2021! You invested your time, energy, mind and heart in the offsite topics and each other. We appreciate the opportunity for transparency, communication and idea sharing around two of our most important upcoming initiatives between the Brand Relaunch and WH Live. We're both excited to be aligned, looking forward to building out integrated marketing plans together, and thrilled to be on this journey with each of you. Onward we go! Z & Amy\n\n108#Seeking Ideas and Perspective from the Sparkle ERG|Jill - I wanted to commend your recent post on the Sparkle Slack channel where you asked for ideas to help Workhuman commemorate BP's award for \"Best place to work for LGBT + Equality.\"  This is such a great example of seeking new perspectives within our Workhuman ERGs. Our groups can help so many parts of the business and provide a ideal focus group - for not only their range of ideas but also their keen expertise for the subject matter within the ERG.  No doubt that the \"moment\" that is created will be even more impactful because of the insight you sought. Well done!   Kevin\n\n109#Wednesday night Zoom-around|Thanks everyone for showing up and contributing to a warm, fun and insightful zoom-around on Wednesday.  Not the same as an in-person conversation, of course but i really enjoyed spending some work-free time with you.  I hope you enjoyed listening and contributing to the 2 lies and 1 truth game we played .... never ceases to amaze me what stories we all have to tell and share.\n\n110#Amazing Breakouts!!|Many thanks to each of you who answered the call for breakout presenters.  You bravely came forward to share your knowledge, experience and expertise with our humans as part of Ignite 2021.  You spent countless hours preparing your sessions, designing slides and learning the ins and outs of Zoom technology all while adjusting to my many (and often changing) reminders!  We were able to offer a wide variety of topics and formats to all our Ignite attendees because of your efforts.  You did all this while still having all the typical demands of your job and your life.  Thank you for your commitment to providing a quality experience to your session participants that gave them tools, ideas and inspiration!\n\n111#Crafty Comms!|Jill, thank you for such a thoughtful and comprehensive Ignite breakout session today!  It was full of great insights, tips and resources with a side of humor and real-life applications.  You are truly a wealth of knowledge and excellent at your craft.  I appreciated having this dedicated time to dive deeper into the art of effective communication and look forward to putting the takeaways into practice! Thanks again!\n\n112#Breakout!|Jon, Jill, Stacey - On behalf of Patti and myself we wanted to recognize and say thank you for taking on individual break out session leadership during Ignite Day 2! Creating and giving people access to these forums helps them invest, learn, and grow. So important! Each of you bring expertise and SME-level knowledge to key areas like: wellness, social, and communications. Thank you for making the time to develop content and lead these sessions today. This was also a great professional development opportunity for each of you ‚Äì proactively taking on risks/embracing new opportunities outside of BAU! With gratitude, -C\n\n113#Interview Extraordinaires!|Team, I wanted to take a quick moment to say thank you for all your help in the interview process for the Marketing Coordinator role. It was SO helpful to have all of your perspectives and insights on each candidate we spoke with.  I appreciate all the time and effort you dedicated to helping us find the right candidate for the role.  After quite a few interviews, we found a great candidate and I couldn't have done it without you! Thanks again!\n\n114#New Year Goals|Thank you all for providing your feedback on the speakers bureau as we closed out 2020. This recognition is long overdue (holiday brain) but it was extremely helpful to hear your goals for the new year to better understand how the bureau can support upcoming projects with speaking engagements. Whether you walked us through a planning deck,