meline and more about the next steps. Our customer has EVERYTHING she could possibly want in order to get approval. Thank you for advocating for customers and moving so quickly and efficiently. I hope we get to start 2021 off with their story!\n\n119#Truly Thoughtful!|Jill, thank you for including Anne and I in your team holiday get together today.  It was such a fun time with a mix of OG and NG (new guard).  Being on the events side, there has been so much flux in 2020.  Sort of a team, but also sort of fragmented.  Anne and I in particular have been a bit of an overlay for demand and customer all year, but not officially on either team.  You were so thoughtful to include us both as a natural part of your customer team ‚Äì and we truly had so much fun reconnecting with everyone.  Thank you so very much!\n\n120#Always going above and beyond!|Jill I wanted to say thank you for all you do for our team. You go above and beyond to make our team feel heard, seen and appreciated. Always making time to catch up, check-in and ensure we have everything we need to be successful. Not only that, you‚Äôve found a way to make Zoom fun again (did I just say that??). From sending lunch for a long planning meeting to breakout rooms so everyone has the space to share their perspectives, fun holiday packages and an even more fun holiday zoom party - I don‚Äôt know how you do it. I also love that you don‚Äôt just think of our team but you think of others as well. You‚Äôre a great example of a leader. Thanks for all you do!!\n\n121#Virtual Holiday Planning!|BIG shoutout for planning the best virtual holiday party! You've made the absolute best of the situations thrown our way in 2020 and we are SO grateful for the planning and coordination that went into it!\n\n122#Team POV (Yeah, you know me) Leaders|Jay and Jill - this is overdue for sure, but thank you for taking the lead on the Pulse Survey action group for the POV team.  You both jumped in to organize the group, put together slides to outline and organize the issues and wrangled the team together to share feedback and propose solutions.  In addition to everything you've both got going on in your \"day jobs\", you stepped up to take the lead on this \"extracurricular\" project.  It shows what great leaders and examples you are for all of us.\n\n123#But you \"made it work\" in 2020!|Team - Tim Gunn was right! We had very ambitious plans for 2020! And then they all changed to a \"different set\" of \"very ambitious\" endeavors and goals ... and you thrived, moved the organization forward to growth, and made sure businesses knew what's next, started now! Thank you for major contributions like: Implementing a data-driven approach to lead generation and pipeline growth resulting in significant growth of MQLs to 10,000!; Launching our first-ever TV and OTT ads; Helping executives unlock grand gestures of gratitude through Team Awards; Developing and delivering two WHLs (albeit in very different ways than originally planned); And helping grow our Employee Experience to rank on the Great Places to Work in 2020! Way to rock it out in 2020, and show 2021 a preview of what a human centered, impact driven approach looks like. Thank you for a terrific year of results, teamwork, support of our stakeholder partners, and resiliency through and through. With gratitude, -C\n\n124#Blood, sweat and tears|Jill and Chris, I cannot thank you enough for all the effort and energy you have been putting into building our customer pipeline for webinars (and all other marketing activities!). It feels at times like we‚Äôre trying to climb Mt Everest on stilts, but nevertheless we are making progress because of all you‚Äôre putting into it. Between our weekly catch-ups, the quick slack updates throughout the day, the customer stories squad, the meetings and conversations you‚Äôre having with CSMs, SCDs, Alice and the content team to make these webinars happen‚Ä¶you‚Äôve given this so much of your attention (likely blood, sweat and tears too) and I hope you know how appreciative we all are for that! It‚Äôs a tricky dance we have to play with getting our customers on-board for these types of opportunities and you‚Äôre doing an amazing job. We never would have gotten Merck, Citizens or Baystate Health to share their stories  without your significant efforts. Thank you for all of it. I'm so grateful to being working with you both on this important initiative!\n\n125#C Ya L8r 2020!|As we head into next year, I feel so aligned with our team, and I'm so excited to tackle new challenges that come our way. You have both been a tireless advocate for us throughout the year and I wanted to thank you for such a successful year of challenges and changes. Our teams has gone from a 3 person tiny team to a fully functioning Customer Development crew. Thank you both for being such incredible leaders - can't wait to see what 2021 has in store for us!\n\n126#Action Planning our way to 2021|Rebecca, Traci, and Kristen, thanks to each of you for coming together and creating our action plans for Strategic Accounts from a S&C, Cx, and a Marketing perspective. Getting us all singing from the same song sheet is imperative for meeting our Moonshots for 2021. Thank you for diving in especially during the craziest end of year we've ever had. I'm so looking forward to working our plan and to celebrating success. Jill and Alice, thank you for supporting this effort and for your insights!\n\n127#On Wednesdays, We Meet, We Talk, We Think, We Act.|And then we do it all over again the following week. I am grateful for your commitment to our Marketing Leadership call week in and week out. Sure, we might not have 52 weeks on the books for 2020, but we MOST DEFINITELY have twice that many hours and then some between our regular weekly meetings and our virtual offsite time together. Focus group of 1 here, but I find the time we spend together immensely valuable - hearing about what various teams are working on, gathering different points of view, discussing ways we can work better together, learning from each of you as subject matter experts and awesome marketers and humans...and last but not least, strengthening the connections between us even though we have been working apart since the early days of March. Enjoy a couple weeks off and we'll assemble again before you know it! THANK YOU!\n\n128#Ready for a New Year!|Thanks to this very focused team of experts and leaders for creating something out of the tough 'hand' 2020 dealt us. Through all we've maneuvered through, I've consistently heard nothing but determination, strength, support for each other and for others, and a fierceness to overcome that is burned in my memory forever. As we 'close' out this year, you've once again dug deep and positioned us for more growth in 2021 though insightful planning and visionary thinking. Spending as much time as possible making things happen leaves little time for planning so all the more impressive how thoroughly you prepared to review action plans for each of your accounts. Thanks to our badass team of magicians, Traci and Rebecca for helping me pull off one of our greatest QBRs to date. Cheers to you all and to many more years of success together! You are all the magic of Christmas!\n\n129#2020 WH Holiday!|Just to tag on a few more thank you's... Jill - if you hadn't pulled the cross-functional group together and got us through that initial brainstorm, we wouldn't have ended up with this all encompassing plan - thank you! Angela, thank you for staying on top of all the moving pieces! We all know that when multiple departments are involved, things can rapidly change but you kept everyone and everything in line until the very last detail was done! Amanda - I am not sure how you managed to compile a list of so many different people in our \"community\" but you did! Thank you for helping to orchestrate something \"for the first time\"... you always seem to be a part of those types of projects. :)\n\n130#Words simply can't describe your leadership style|Jill, I was trying to find a word (or set of words) to describe and recognize everything you're doing for us - but I end up with a long laundry list of characteristics and behaviors. This year, you've guided us to crush every objective, held us accountable, empowered us to think differently and most importantly enjoyed the journey and laughed throughout. I personally can't thank you enough for all that you do, and rather than attach a CSV of the laundry list - I will just simply say thank you for all that you are doing and continually pushing us to improve ourselves!!\n\n131#Lights, Camera, Action Groups!|Team - Z and I want to thank you all for your work getting the Pulse Survey Action Groups kicked off. Your ideas we so thoughtful and well crafted for the short window we gave you. We are beyond impressed! As Chris said, this is hugely important work and it is ongoing. We are excited to continue our partnership with you as we build and develop out these programs! We are grateful for you all!\n\n132#Story Tellers|I can't describe the amazing feelings this team created when we all shared our personal stories and our vulnerabilities to each other.  There was a wonderful sense of connection and support that allowed us to create something special between everyone.  I know it wasn't easy (trust me!) and I want to thank all of you for taking the time to be open, honest and emotional.  There is no other company I have ever worked for that has had this connection between employees, and it was so incredibly special..  I am so happy to be a part of #teamawesome with all of you!\n\n133#Grateful for all you do!|As this time of thanks rolls around, I wanted to express sincerest gratitude for you. Having worked together on recent projects I have seen how you go above and beyond for every task, which shines through the end results. Have a wonderful, happy and safe Thanksgiving. I'm looking forward to continuing to work with you in the rest of 2020 and beyond!\n\n134#Unwavering Support System|\"I am surrounded by the most supportive people who genuinely care about my development as a person and as a young professional\" - This was a text I sent my mom lol (I'm so lame). That being said, I wanted to thank you all for your seeing me, hearing me and offering me so much love and support throughout the second half of this year. This pandemic is rough on everyone for different reasons, but we need to help each other up during this time - and you have all been there for me throughout this process. Kristen, Thank you for being there to listen to me when I was struggling, stressed and confused. You helped me find solutions and brought in other individuals who were willing to help as well. I never thought it was possible to connect with a manager like this, but you make me feel so comfortable around you. Thank you for that. Jill, I wanted to thank you for your concerns and providing such sought-after advice -  you are always SO willing to help, no matter what. As our team grows, It has been amazing to get closer to work with you on projects and connect as humans. Tyler, Thank you for speaking with me and allowing me to pick your brain with all my questions! Hearing your personal stories and listening to your professional growth throughout the years is so reassuring. I am so lucky to be surrounded by people who genuinely care about my growth as a person and I know I am exactly where I should be. Thank you all!!!\n\n135#Thanks for your commitment to this journey!|Huge shout out to our esteemed colleagues on the inaugural Experience Task Force team!   Thank you for all of your support, patience, persistence, passion, participation, and continued commitment to the journey we're on together.  We know that the road hasn't always been clear, and perhaps a little bumpy while we've figured out how to navigate, but we've gotten to our first set of priority ideas to tackle for the buyer journey, which is