 do so in the spirit of inter-dependence and collaboration.  You all definitely delivered on that and it sets us up well for 2021.  I'm proud to be alongside you on this journey.  Onward and upward!\n\n138#2021 Marketing Planning Pros!|So, we didn‚Äôt quite spend 6 hours together today but pretty close to it! Add in previous working sessions, the pre-work PLUS the work to come, and we will easily surpass that. BUT in the end, we'll be poised and ready to execute a solid plan for the new year. We appreciate your commitment to the 2021 marketing planning process. We‚Äôre taking a different approach this year and we‚Äôre coming close to the 10-month mark of working remotely during an epic year of CRAZY. With so many players involved, different points of view, and known foundational gaps like solid messaging ‚Äì (YES, we know, we know!)‚Ä¶it‚Äôs not an easy task. We are optimistic about the progress we‚Äôre making together. We are grateful for your focus on the end goal and how we'll get there. Thank you for partnering with us to sharpen our strategies and set our teams up to properly support the business in 2021. Onward we go! Z + Amy\n\n139#Supporting our customer team|Jill and Allison, thank you for taking the time today to discuss how we can be better at supporting the customer team when it comes to events.  You both were thoughtful and reflective in taking a step back and looking at how we work together, the specific needs of the team, resources, timing, and in general considering alternatives to make overall improvements that will drive us toward stronger performance in 2021.  It was a great discussion that I look forward to acting on for the next big event.\n\n140#A Team Approach to Professional Development|These days we are all under the same time restraints and stresses, but that wasn‚Äôt going to stop these rockstar teams from focusing on growth and development!  It was motivating to watch everyone quickly come together to tackle a multi-day, multi-session conference ‚Äì making it possible to consume hours worth of content in a fraction of the time.  Thank you for thoughtfully recapping your sessions and sharing key findings.  The takeaways and ideas were inspiring and will help expedite the growth of our customer experience and marketing efforts.  And a special shout-out to Becky for organizing the entire process and keeping us on track!\n\n141#Pinky Swear!|Jill, I pinky swear... I will put a note on my calendar to think about the holiday card planning in early October of 2021. :) Love starting off a meeting with pinky swears. Seriously though, the way you brought the team together today to talk about the Holiday Greeting Strategy was impressive. You recognized this takes effort across various teams so you were sure to be inclusive. We talked about the needs of Customers, Future Customers and vendors, what's been done in the past, and what would make the most of our audience's experience this year. It was an effective meeting with a purposeful agenda to lock down ownership, strategy, and deliverables. Then, you shared your follow on notes which blew me away! Thank you for truly owning this project and giving it a great start!\n\n142#Congrats, you're a sinner!|WOO!! or should i say BOO!! Congrats to all our winners from this years Halloween slack events. Well done to you all for your participation and effort, Customer Marketing your submission was hilarious and on theme for our Murder Mystery event. Genessa with your delicious looking 4 legged s'more. Rich and batcat absolutely nailed it! Megan your little pup is just too cute and pretty popular, we're waiting for the instagram...Zhennaa we loved the door dress up, a level up on halloween decoration. Eileen, that zoom themed pumpkin was just too 2020 and it spooked us and Colleen in addition to this your life time supply of Oil of Olay is on the way.\n\n143#Ah ... Break out! (Don't freak out)|Z, Jill - Masterful job today introducing some \"next level\" technology for our Customer Marketing all hands. When we discussed the idea of simultaneous multiple break out rooms, you did not \"FREAK OUT\" - you stayed cool, and found a way to make it happen. Because of your willingness to try something new and put a new idea into action, we had an incredibly productive, fun, and even \"breezy\" 90-minute all hands. Well done and with gratitude, -C\n\n144#Stupendous Support!!!|Jill and Kristen, it's so very hard to keep up with all the recognition you two deserve!  It seems like a VERY broad idea pops into my head and you two take it, run with it and develop it into something amazing and impactful!  Our bp \"Thank You\" video was perfection that was complimented all the way up to the CEO of bp in writing!!  You just can't get better than that!  You have helped with so many ideas, campaigns, drives etc all with enthusiasm and, best of all, with a ton of fun and excitement.  Your energy and zeal is infectious.  I so appreciate all the support and pure joy you both bring to the table.  Thank you so very much!\n\n145#Congrats Workhuman Live Team!|Team ‚Äì A HUGE shout out to each of you for helping deliver a fantastic event yesterday. It truly was amazing! Your hard work and dedication to excellence have set a NEW example for everyone in our organization. I‚Äôm inspired by the ingenuity and creativity of everyone‚Äôs contribution ‚Äì planning, marketing, storytelling, vendor management, customer support, technical execution, and so much more. Your efforts have allowed us to create a new conversation in the marketplace. I‚Äôm genuinely excited to build on this shared momentum to help every organization bring people closer together. None of this would be possible without YOU. I extend my heartiest congratulations on achieving a fantastic milestone. Well done ALL!\n\n146#Workhuman Certified Superstars|The words ‚Äúthank you,‚Äù can‚Äôt begin to express the gratitude Brenda and I have for this team of talented colleagues who we‚Äôve had the pleasure of working with to bring the Workplace Charter of Rights and Workhuman Certified to life. Whether you‚Äôve been on this journey with us for the past year or the past month, you‚Äôve all had a hand in helping us achieve our vision of changing the workplace for good. Our Marketing friends set the stage for success with a strong go-to-market strategy & brand design, an engaging web presence with compelling copy, customer pioneers to validate our program and tell their stories and customer ‚Äúfriendlies‚Äù to preview the program, influencer briefings, securing previous WH Live videos, and so much more! Our HR team challenged our new way of thinking about HR programs, helping to shape the Enterprise application process and ensuring we as a company were demonstrating progress in the Rights, while also preparing to educate and inform employees about this new initiative. And behind the scenes, our very own legal eagles were there to ensure everyone‚Äôs best interests were kept in mind. This is the largest cross-functional project we‚Äôve been part of during our time at Workhuman, and we couldn‚Äôt be more proud of what we‚Äôve been able to accomplish together. The saying is true‚Ä¶teamwork really does make the dream work! Thank you, all!\n\n147#Existing Customer Marketing Recaps - On Point!|Jill - I was just reading your weekly marketing recap...First of all - the work you and your team are focused on is in a word - PHENOMENAL. When you look at how much customers contribute to our overall bookings, you realize how ALL. THE. THINGS. you are driving from a marketing standpoint has a real impact on our business. Secondly, I suspect it takes a fair amount of time and energy to pull your recaps together but let me tell you, it's so lovely to have it all in one place - a treasure trove of bite size nuggets of content with visuals and hyperlinks to assets and/or more detail. We all know we can't all be everywhere all the time. Fortunately, for me your email is such a useful communication vehicle that helps me think about potential points of integration and in general, stay connected to all the amazing work your team is doing. I am sure I am not alone but I wanted to officially thank you for keeping us informed. I appreciate and look forward to your recap each week.\n\n148#Supporting All Things Customer Success|Ladies, this is a long overdue gratitude for all that you have helped support over the past few weeks and months.  Whether we have needed creative help for Here 2 Help or a campaign for the WH.com migration both of you have always been ready and willing to jump in.  Without your support we would not be able to showcase a polished one pager to help the triage support model pop.  Your creative juices are flowing and I truly believe this will help our Customers transition that much faster.  So, thank you for all your help and support.  We would not be ready for the next phase in Q1 without both of you!\n\n149#What is a stronger word for supportive?|To say that you have been a supportive manager over the last 7.5 months is an understatement.  In a time of great uncertainty and in this highly charged environment, you have gone out of your way to ensure that myself and the entire team feel connected, appreciated and useful.  You‚Äôve led by example ‚Äì setting up office hours, supplying agendas for all team meetings and providing notes that keep us all informed.  We more than doubled in size during this pandemic and we did so without massive growing pains because of your transparent, communicative and caring work style.  Thank you for taking the time to check in on our well-being, for strategically distributing workloads or for your constant understanding and flexibility.  Customer retention is more important than ever and I‚Äôm confident that under your leadership we are destined for great things.  Thank you, Jill!\n\n150#CAE Customer Spotlight|Jill, Chris - I wanted to give you both a shoutout for meeting with CAE last week and putting together a thoughtful, personalized deck on ways to highlight them as a company.  Lisa sent me a message afterwards excited about the possibility of making your ideas happen.  For me personally, I love to see that we not only value our client's partnerships, but we truly value the the work our customers do for their communities and their employees.  If that's not a sign Workhuman is a true partner, I don't know what is!  Celebrating our customer's achievements is a small thing we can do as a company, but it matters and is appreciated.  Also, an additional thank you for quickly shipping a copy of Making Work Human to all of them.  I know CAE shares our philosophy of bringing humanity back to the workplace and I'm excited about the future of our partnership.\n\n151#Offsite virtually, but totally productive day IRL!|Team ‚Äì Thank you for your active participation in our 2nd planning ‚Äúvirtual‚Äù offsite. The energy level was high and the level of engagement and strategic thinking was strong. Patti and I are excited about the united approach to not only long-term marketing planning, but building a strong culture for the entire Marketing team where different points of view are embraced and we are continually testing new ways of working to optimize our contributions to overall business results. I‚Äôm genuinely excited to build on this shared momentum to bring our 2021 plans to life. With gratitude ‚Äì C.\n\n152#üôåüèª Upleveling our Team Updates üôåüèª|Week in and week out, each of you contribute to a few different communication vehicles we have to keep our team and stakeholders across the company up to date on all the amazing things that are happening in the world of Marketing. About a month or so ago, I came to the team with a new process for pulling together our weekly updates and challenged each of us to think about the intended audience and what would be most valuable to them...We started including more metrics and other performance data in our look-backs and introduced headlines to provide more focus. We are also incorporating more visuals to keep the content fresh and engaging. We held each other accountable to sticking to a standard template and hitting deadlines so that we could get the updates edited and out the door in a timely fashion. I know between the weekly marketing updates, the digital programming status reports and ELT progress updates, you probably feel like this is communication overload at times, but they are important in staying connected and current especially when we are all remote. I sincerely appreciate your part in helping to improve the quality. THANK YOU!\n\n153#What a Team, What a Q3!|Biggest of shout outs to this team of strategic thinkers and leaders! After a much needed 4th of July breather, this team came roaring back and starting blasting moonshots right out of the gate...securing meetings with some of our biggest customers to recruit them to be early adopters of our next gen DEI functionality, recruiting Pioneers for the WHCE, leading SO MANY strategic customer reviews with senior leaders, and killing it with multiple major deals! A team of super heroes! So proud of the work that you're doing and WE STILL HAVE ANOTHER QUARTER TO GO!\n\n154#Making gratitude look easy|Team, thank you all for your incredible ingenuity, creativity, partnership and support in helping to pull together all the customer resources for World Gratitude Day.  Each of you helped compile all the relevant materials that the Customer Success team was able to easily share out with customers in highlighting creative ways to celebrate this day.  I had never seen such a coordinated and detailed approach in packaging up materials that could so readily be put out into the hands of our customers.  Not only that, but you topped that off with coming up with such a great email to send to our customers celebrating them on World Gratitude Day.  The thoughtful approach you took in pulling this together was so impactful yet so simple to execute really had an impact on hundreds of our program teams.  You made it so easy for the Customer Success team to pull together a heartfelt message along with a picture or video thanking our customers for the opportunities we have to work with the world's best companies.  We received so many wonderful messages back from our program teams calling out how much they appreciated the partnership with Workhuman.  I am thankful for each of you and your help in executing a powerful number of moments that mattered for our clients.\n\n155#Partnering On Linkedin and Cisco DNI Opportunities|Chris and Jill, this is more than a thank you. This is an OMG, YOU TWO ARE THE MOST INCREDIBLY TALENTED, CREATIVE, AND WICKEDLY FUN PEOPLE TO COLLABORATE WITH, IN THE WHOLE WIDE WORLD!  Marie and I came to you with a passion project: What if we could get the CDO at Cisco and the CDO at Linkedin on a virtual stage to share their thought leadership on building and sustaining inclusive and equitable cultures? And you both immediately embraced our dream as your own.   I mean, talk about taking an idea and running with it. You took what was a rough draft and helped develop a full fledged package. Thank you for taking the lead on creating the pitch deck, helping hone the value prop and positioning statements, and mapping out a comprehensive marketing strategy.   As if that wasn't enough, you came back with multiple abstracts to showcase the breadth and depth of our thinking to both CDOs, as well as innovative ways to get these incredibly important stories out to the masses.   And, Chris, I am blown away by your uncanny ability to not miss one single detail. You've kept us all aligned and progressing forward. Because of you, the momentum hasn't slowed down one bit. I can't tell you how fulfilling it is to partner with you both and how excited I am to see this all come to fruition.\n\n156#Shining the Spotlight on Baystate Health|Chris, Patti & Jill - we're embarking on an exciting opportunity to help showcase all the ways our client Baystate Health truly exemplifies working human - with the ultimate goal of generating a multi-channel \"good news\" communications package. We had a successful brainstorming call with their CHRO and VP of Marketing & Comms yesterday, and your contributions were the instrumental in sparking sincere interest from Baystate in collaborating with us on this project. Chris, you set the table for the conversation perfectly by reinforcing how much we value their partnership (5 years strong at this point) and why we want to share the remarkable story of how they've made their employees feel seen, heard and valued during these difficult pandemic times. Patti, you impressed them with your passion for telling these types of stories across our clients, and explaining why we believe Baystate to be at the forefront of organizations who truly embrace a culture of recognition and gratitude. Jill, you've been an amazing partner to work with on this project, always willing and available to offer your insights and top-notch content. Thanks to each of you. I'm excited to see where this project goes, and your contributions and leadership have set us up to be successful.\n\n157#GLG World Gratitude Day|Team, thank you so much for all of your help making the GLG WGD live stream a success. It started as a small idea from the client, and today everything came to life with your help. Lynette, you were so amazing on the live stream discussing Work Human and speaking with GLG's CHRO. Thank you everyone for bringing this idea to life, I am so grateful!\n\n158#Hello Workday!|Thank you for being an early adopter of Workday and for completing your scavenger hunt by the end of our first day officially live!!\n\n159#Making it all about THEM|Thank you for meeting earlier this week to wrestle with the eternal question: \"What matters most to senior leaders at our top accounts?\".  The thoughtful, candid and creative ideas you brought to the table are going to help immensly as we develop the Insider Insights session for our key accounts.  And when we put customers at the center and consider their perspective, we guarantee success!\n\n160#I'm Grateful for YOU!!!!|To the AMAZING World Gratitude Day team - you have inspired me to start my gratitude journal right here, right now. (1) I'm grateful for the fantastic collaboration between strategy and consulting and customer marketing for the ideation, creation and execution of our World Gratitude Day strategic plan. The FIRST of many collaborations to transform the way our customers experience, receive, consume and act on our messaging. Thank you Jill, Kristen, and Melissa K for the many calls, brainstorming, planning and execution of our 3 phased approach! Our collaboration set a new standard for the word collaboration - open communication, skill-sharing, goal alignment, engagement, problem solving and being agile. (2) I'm grateful for Lynette, Amanda, Melissa F and Sarah who's strengths and talents were on full display during this entire engagement. Lynnette, thank you for your eloquent writing skills, pro-actively jumping in and producing high quality materials nearly overnight. Amanda, thank you for your strategic mindset, seeing ahead to the final vision, translating needs into actionable steps for the team, and working along side of me at what probably seemed like hourly the last 24 hours. Melissa F, thank you for always being a tremendous partner, thinking through every detail, trying out new technology, making the process as easy as possible for CSMs and smiling through the numerous rounds of edits, link checks, and late night madness! Sarah, your creative skills lead the way with the WGD visual campaign consisting of not one, but two, concept options, the WeTransfer personalized background and much more! (3) I'm grateful for our customers like Merck, UHG and Schneider Electric who within minutes of receiving the email with the toolkit stated they can't wait to leverage a number of the assets in the toolkit!! Gratitude is a wonderful thing. It makes what is EXCELLENT in others belong to us as well!! Thank you for sharing your excellence with me and the world!! YOU ROCK!!\n\n161#7 Habits ‚ÄìFramingham Graduates ‚ÄìClass of June 2020|‚ÄúMOTIVATION is what gets you started. HABIT is what keeps you going.\" - Jim Rohn.   To appreciate and recognise our Framingham based humans' commitment, hard work and valuable participation, please join me in congratulating each of them for investing in their personal development and successfully completing ‚ÄòThe 7 Habits of Highly Effective People‚Äô programme this week.  On a personal level, it has been a genuine privilege to have guided you all through this course and I wish to THANK YOU for your determination, innovation, collaboration and above all, the kindness you showed to one another and to me.  In turn you helped create and nurture a positive environment of trust and respect, where everyone‚Äôs uniqueness was truly valued.   Habit 7 - YOU are your single greatest asset so continue to invest in your 'Four Dimensions of Renewal' because when your Body, Mind, Heart and Spirit are nourished, all four will flourish!  Thank you FRAMINGHAM :) Donna\n\n162#Finishing Strong!|I wanted to take a moment to congratulate you both on officially completing our Franklin Covey training course today. Wahoo, we did it!!!  From beginning to end, you have both been so invested in this program and it has had such a tremendous impact on the way you have lead our team. Being a part of this course with you has been inspiring and has pushed me to get the most out of it. Show up and get the most out of the classes. Yes, it was time consuming, but you always managed to make the time and finish strong and make it through until the end. It has been so amazing to see both of you apply your learnings to our everyday lives at Workhuman. Keep it up!!\n\n163#Virtual Offsite - but 100% Productive IRL|Team - On behalf of Patti and myself thank you for a tremendous Q3 strategic planning and execution offsite last week. Both presenters and discussion partners excelled in their roles to communicate and strengthen existing plans. Your engagement and participation was locked in for the full session. And it's exciting to see this team rally around a new way of working that is oriented toward connecting business results to the strategic objectives of all our 2H initiatives within Marketing and across partner stakeholder teams. Thanks for leaning into the process - it's becoming a difference maker for us and helping us cut through our own noise! -C\n\n164#Marketing Leadership|Jill ‚Äì this recognition is long overdue. I want to acknowledge the leadership you have shown, not only on the marketing team, but in the organization. Your commitment to building and executing on a robust customer marketing plan is admirable. You clearly define your goals, strategy, and tactics, and take the time to communicate these to the team. You take a collaborative approach to working with your colleagues, and are always prepared, present, and on time to Zoom meetings. This demonstrates great respect to everyone‚Äôs time, which is precious given the volume of deliverables we each have. I appreciate your partnership with how content ties into your campaigns, and you take the time to talk through what is working while identifying gaps. Keep up the excellent work and thanks for all you do.\n\n165#Our Fearless Leaders!|Jill and Kristen I wanted to take a moment to thank you two for all your hard work that has gone into Q3 planning and beyond. SERIOUSLY, you guys are crushing it! I see how much time and effort that has gone into these plans and they are so well thought out. It feels so good to know that Customer Development has a fully-baked plan of attack for the coming months, and it is so nice to work proactively for a change!! You guys are so inspiring and I wanted to let you know that I am so grateful to learn from two bad A$$ lady leaders! Q3 has no idea whats coming!!\n\n166#Finding our social diamond in the rough|I want to thank you all for being an amazing interview panel for our director of social media position. You each are bringing amazing perspectives and insights into the role and your feedback is so incredibly valuable. We've got high standards to ensure we bring in the right candidate that is going to elevate this team, grow this function and be that wonderful team lead. While we haven't found them (yet!), I am so grateful to your candid feedback and commitment to working with us on getting to that gem.\n\n167#Teamwork makes the dream work!|Team - so excited to see the collaborative work, cross-functional thinking and strategic planning going into our 2H approach. It is holistic, considers the bigger picture, and was well articulated. Look out Q3, here we come! -C\n\n168#Chip Chip Chipping away to deliver SUCCESS!|Jill, I want to take a second to say a HUGE thank you for the sheer determination, positive energy, and effort that you have put in to partnering on the Customer Story project with me.  You sought to understand the win win we needed to obtain for sales, marketing, customer success and of course the customer! Trying to align 3 department's needs in a cohesive way to deliver an exciting and customized customer facing deck that best positions our desire to celebrate our customers for working human in a way that plants seeds for Workhuman Certified and delivers sales enablement and marketing assets that are exciting, innovative and desirable is NO SMALL FEAT!  Thank you for your determination to make it happen, for your commitment to quality and for your speed in engaging with the relevant teams to lay the foundation that we needed in place!  We are off to a great start and now with the help of brand and creative we are almost there!  Like this picture there have been many times that it seemed that we had reached a dead end but each time we dusted ourselves off and pivoted as needed!  Thank you for not letting the frustrations get to you and for being a GREAT partner!  I love being in the trenches with you!  We are nearly there, and it will be AMAZING!  Thank you!\n\n169#Winning!|Jill, over the last few months as we have all worked to adjust to this new way of life (and work), I have noticed time and time again how you go above and beyond. Although I've never lived through a pandemic, I've experienced instances where people have the opportunity to shine and to lead when maybe others cannot. You have been steadfast in your leadership! While so many others keep asking 'is 2020 over yet?' joking or not, you have embraced it and continued to deliver at the highest level. You are a no excuse, get sh*t done kinda gal and we love you for it! I am sometimes almost speechless (I know rare!) when i join and see all that you have STILL managed to tackle against the odds. Here there and everywhere!. What pandemic? You must not sleep. Thank you for all that you are doing, every bit of effort you put into every call, interaction and project. You and the team you have built are producing work that is turning heads ... because it is amazing. THANK YOU!\n\n170#Non-stop Jill!|Jill - This is very overdue. ...Honestly, do you sleep? üòâ With so many moving parts, you are always responding to the constant WorkFront updates at ALL hours. Since the pandemic, you and your team have been tasked with how to reach our customers given the \"new normal\". You are forward-thinking with all these initiatives, and willing to collaborate across departments to get the best results. In addition, as we're trying to implement new processes, you're always onboard and willing to partner with the project management team. Thank you for all your hard work for our customer outreach, for being a great team player, and for always implementing the comic relief along the way.\n\n171#Putting the \"Lift off\" in \"Kick off\"|Team - as workplaces everywhere contemplate the next phase of work, we are leading the way in what that looks like externally and with our customers. It also means we need to evolve internally. I was so impressed by the team work and open mindedness demonstrated by this cross-functional group in today's kick off! So, as they say, \"Houston, we have lift off!\" Excited to see where this group takes the next phase of what it means to thrive and workhuman. With gratitude, -C\n\n172#A true moment that mattered!|All, On behalf of the entire HR team, we want to thank you so much for the amazing video you put together for us! The team was speechless, so shocked and also so incredibly grateful to all who took the time to make this happen. This is what moments that matter is all about... a true human moment of surprise and delight but more important, genuine care. The HR team Slack channel was  buzzing after the video played, with heartfelt messages from the team, so wanted to share some of the sentiments.. \"What a moment of \"surprise & delight\" indeed! It's rare HR gets a shout out, let alone a dedicated video. Very sweet and thoughtful.\" \"I am speechless.. just wow\" \"I was bawling.. so sweet.. goosebumps\" \"i am pretty blown away by that\" \"Lovely surprise! Well done team!\" \"the genuine appreciation was so evident.\" \"the video made my Friday and reminded us why what all of us do here is so special!!\"  Thank you all again for taking the time to think of us, for creating this very special moment and for living our values to the fullest!  Much love, your humans behind the humans!\n\n173#Open and Honest|Thank you for allowing there to be an open dialogue with both myself and the team as a whole. The openness and honesty that we have is like none other and it allows us all to be able to speak up and tell you what we really feel. That's a very special thing and I'm grateful I'm in a place where I can make my voice heard without being afraid to do so.\n\n174#First impressions|Jill - a quick shoutout to you for all thought and energy you've put into up-leveling the various marketing presentations our team gives to our new hires. You put for a recommendation to all the Marketing directors last week, gathered input from all of us and collaborated with Sharon to make sure that our streamlined and cohesive approach would meet the objectives of the onboarding program for Workhuman. We all know from firsthand experience that there's a lot to digest as a new hire and you've made sure we share the right level of information at the right time. Now the fun part begins in creating the new presentation materials based on the foundation you've established for us! This project has been on the back burner for a while without an official owner, so I really admire and appreciate the initiative you have taken to improve our department's first impression to new humans that join our family. Thank you for your leadership!\n\n175#Tried and True Teammate|Jill, when I think of a person who is ever-reliable, responsive, and ready to help in whatever way possible, you are at the top of that list. I want to thank you for continuously and consistently being someone to rely on, even when it's out of the scope of your day to day - and especially when you're juggling a million and one other things. You are always at the ready to patiently answer questions and give clarity around customer projects. You hop on calls at the drop of a hat. You answer slacks within seconds. You are poised to roll up your sleeves at any given moment to get something done, even if it's for a project you're not running. Just this week I've come to you a few times to nail down some tasks. You also offered to facilitate getting customer quote approval for an acquisition project. All of this you do without hesitation, but instead with a completely genuine team spirit and the best of humor. You're awesome and I don't tell you enough, but I sure appreciate you and all you do for this department.\n\n176#Customer Champion|You are the ultimate customer champion!  Thanks so much for all the time dedicated to reviewing the Livestream follow up plans for customers - helping guide me through the different segment needs and always being available to provide feedback, direction, and recommendations.  Even when you're on PTO!  It's always a pleasure to collaborate with you and I especially appreciate your help on the Livestream project!\n\n177#Keeping Humanity Alive with Live!|Team ‚Äì Thank you for delivering a high quality, compelling, on brand, and ‚Äúof the moment‚Äù digital event. In less than six weeks you expertly pivoted from the cancellation of our physical events in San Antonio and Dublin and leaped into bold new thinking that resulted in our Workhuman Live Stream event. You were fearless in pursuit of our audacious goal of 10,000 registrants and charged furiously at it ‚Äì obliterating the goal and achieving more than 15,000+ registrants. This level of success took thoughtful planning, decisive and quick action, creativity, and relentless outreach to secure exceptional guest speakers, high profile customer stories, and new sponsorships. There was clear demonstration of teamwork, resilience, grit ‚Äì and quite a bit of ‚Äúgood cheer‚Äù across this group. It was an example of Workhuman at our best. This is a significant achievement in the company‚Äôs history and will continue to pay dividends in the following areas: Social reach; The launch of our new products like Moodtracker; Deepening existing customer relationships; Establishing strong new footholds with future customers; And growing profitably. My hat‚Äôs off to you all ‚Äì when Humanity needed us most ‚Äì you all rallied to give Humanity the company it needed now more than ever. On behalf of the Leadership Team and myself, Thank you - Eric\n\n178#Hand in Glove|Team - we are running at such a high pace that there's always the risk of the left hand not knowing what the right hand is doing. You've demonstrated behaviors and teamwork that is the exact opposite - more like Hand in Glove level of coordination and alignment. Thank you for developing a process \"light\" engagement model for best serving our business while leveraging our customers in a smart and targeted way. More importantly, you clearly outlined and communicated this process effectively and concisely at our Marketing town hall today. With gratitude, -C\n\n179#Powerful Communications Pack a Punch|Eileen, Jill & Kristen,  I wanted to say a huge THANK YOU to each of you for creating an incredible communication tool for the SCDs for the upcoming Livestream.  It was so amazing to have the perfect foundational pieces for our invitations and outreach.  I can't tell you how much easier it was thanks to all of your hard work.  We always hear that teamwork makes the dream work and it couldn't be more true in this instance.  Thank you to all of you, you don't know how much we all appreciated the effort!\n\n180#Leadership Skills Soaring High!|Jill, I just met with your latest 'new hire' who told me that this is his first job out of college. I asked him with zero expectations what he thought customer experience was... so I could gauge where to begin. :) In all the conversations I have had internally and externally with people about what customer experience is... Jeff gave the best/simplest response. I am not sure if it was because I did not expect him to know given he is just starting out and also because so many have it confused (we are on a journey!) but WOW. This goes directly back to you and your amazing leadership. Jeff told me that he had already heard about our team and some projects from you. At a time when things are so chaotic and it is even more challenging to stay connected - you are soaring high. I am super impressed by what he has retained so far and it's only been weeks. You and your team are doing phenomenal despite the obstacles in this new way of working. I can't imagine how difficult it must be to on-board someone and on top of that... it being their very first job. On behalf of CX, thank you for making our job easier!!\n\n181#Wait! Was that really only 90 days?!|Team - Thank you for making this next phase of our journey and evolution together as a team so successful! Lets just say the first 60 day together were much different than our last 30 days together(ish)! Wanted to celebrate all we‚Äôve done together in our first 3 months as a team. Attached is my quick recap and where I see us delivering results in Q2. Thank you, I‚Äôm truly appreciative of all you do!  With gratitude, -C\n\n182#Thoughtful Input for Livestream Follow Up|Fellow marketing peeps - thanks for taking time out of your busy schedules this week to talk through the communication plans for Livestream follow up.  Since the audience for Livestream is so diverse, spanning customers, prospects and SMB groups, the follow up planning needs to deliver the right message to each group to deliver on the business goals.  Your input was invaluable in guiding the direction the plan is taking for each segment.  It's not final yet, but I think we're on the right path and I thank each of you for sharing your thoughts and suggestions with me.  Have a great weekend all!\n\n183#Marketing Rockstars|Jill and Kristen, thank you for everything you‚Äôve done with Dell.   When they started considering internal changes to the program, you took immediate action and (somewhat miraculously) delivered a social surround campaign overnight for their executive team.  I‚Äôm overwhelmed by your endless support and partnership. You ladies spearhead all of the customer marketing opportunities for our top accounts; from account based marketing plans, social surround campaigns, COVID marketing playbooks, WHL recruiting efforts - this list goes on and on! You go over and above to support our team.\n\n184#Keeping Our Ship Afloat|I must commend you both on such an outstanding job you have been doing over these past few weeks. You have continuously managed to keep our team on track, despite the roadblocks and changes we may have hit along the way. Not only have you been handling multiple projects of your own, but you‚Äôve also been able to jump in to help Jeff and I with certain tasks as well.    Kristen, your optimism and honesty have kept me going these past few weeks‚Ä¶ and I mean that! Even our quick little video check-in or encouraging slack gives me the boost I need to push through the day and finish strong. These past few weeks have been hard on everyone and some days are harder than others, but I just wanted to thank you for your patience and encouraging mindset throughout this transition.   Jill, your availability to jump in and help during the Merck Webinar has been tremendously helpful. With this project moving so quickly, it has been a difficult one to reign this one in on my own. You are a wealth of knowledge and I have learned so much from you as our small but mighty customer development team has taken shape. Thank you for always being there to bounce questions off of and keep us informed on all things Workhuman.   With all our unique work schedules and juggling acts, I wanted to let you guys know that you are doing an outstanding job as managers and role models. Thank you!\n\n185#Thank You Healthcare Images - Weekend Worriors|Thank you all for jumping in to take part in the logo and image sourcing and uploading for hospitals into the Thank You Healthcare site!  Ensuring that the experience is personal and meaningful for those who access the site is incredibly important and your help in making this happen was invaluable! I got to see first-hand your passion, collaboration and sheer energy brought to this exciting task!  You gave up time over your Easter weekend with family to dedicate energy toward this grand human cause.  Adam, Becky and Meghan, thank you for leading the cross functional team from activating help from across the company, providing detailed instructions (that even I could follow), guidance, direction, answering questions and providing top tips and learnings throughout the process, even participating as heavy hitters in the uploading and sourcing as well! When I asked you, Becky and Meg, to help partner with Adam and the technology team to make this happen you were so excited to be a part of this phenomenal project and your pride was palpable- thank you!  You guys have become the 3 amigos!  Superb effort, and excellent management, your incredible knowledge and attention to detail has been awe-inspiring! Thank you also to each of you who dedicated an hour, several hours and in some cases most of the weekend to sourcing and uploading!  We so appreciate your efforts!  Many hands make light work, my mother used to say! I do want to call out a few of you who really made an incredible dent in the project uploading and sourcing between 70 and 230 images each and in many cases hitting both uploading and sourcing!  WOW!  Brian Moore, Matt Durgin, John Wamback, Jon Bizeur, Amanda Salvas, Rich Sorrentino, Jillian Gregoriou and Dan Fiore, you guys are complete rock stars and your contributions were mammoth! This was a true team effort and to see it in action makes me so proud to be a part of our Workhuman family!  Amazing job! Let‚Äôs share some gratitude with the world now!\n\n186#A second home (in my basement)|All three of you have done such an awesome job helping me get ramped up the last 3 weeks. Starting remote is definitely a weird feeling but each of you have helped me feel like I have a home here. These are tough times, but I am so grateful to be surrounded by people like you. I can't wait to get to the office and see each one of you in person every day instead of through just a screen! Thank you so much!\n\n187#Urgency + Energy + Intelligence|I wanted to thank this group for your speedy help launching a set of LinkedIn ads for an important customer this week.  You each acted quickly, asked valuable questions and made efficient decisions. And while this request was for just one customer, you‚Äôve worked in a way that will enable us to use this ad set for a larger group.  Working remote can come with challenges, but the communication and fast responses from this group made it easy.  Thank you!\n\n188#LinkedIn Elevate Superheroes|First, all of you deserve a massive round of applause for your extraordinary use of LinkedIn Elevate. You have all won the battle amongst your departments for the most amount of content pushed to your social networks in this past quarter. On top of this, each of you has contributed to a social media tidal wave that has earned the company over $50K in social media value over just Q1 alone and the social team is wildly gracious for this. Elevate has seen great success and it continues with your exemplary use. A big thanks to each of you and a cheer to continued super-user status!\n\n189#Best. Team. Ever.|Thank you for a great Zoom meeting to align around our short term priorities while daring to dream and proactively plan for longer term priorities. Not an easy task to do when the \"here and now\" is all anyone of us can think about lately. I was so impressed with everyone's willingness to think about team resources in a different way and also our shared commitment to the good work and strategic thinking that we already did together pre COVID-19 crisis. This was my most productive meeting of the day and an awesome way to end the week. I am grateful for this awesome team. Thank you!\n\n190#CSR Committee|A heartfelt note of gratitude for your overwhelming and immediate support of our CSR initiative. In the midst of all that is unfolding across the company as we respond to COVID-19, you found the time to join our little committee and came up with several outstanding ideas in no time at all! We are rallying around those ideas and from it will emerge a short and long-term plan to further our impact on lives and communities. Onward and forward!\n\n191#Communication All Stars|Technology should enhance good communication.  You are all getting this award because you have embraced our technology over the last few weeks in the way it was intended. You‚Äôve helped project management in supporting you in projects By uploading docs, putting in requests, communicating and tagging team members.  The way we use this tool today will help us to a more refined way of working as we move forward.   Thank you!\n\n192#Draft after draft|Jill, I know that title sounds exciting.  Unfortunately it's not that kind of draft.  It is version after version of customer communications.  All day.  Every day.  For over a week now.  I couldn't think of anyone better to be alongside on this journey.  I appreciate your commitment to quality, the open and candid feedback, the flexibility in design, the creative input regarding content and especially all the laughs and Slack messages.  I'm grateful for your partnership.\n\n193#CREATING A WAVE of GRATITUDE|Can you feel it? It's a soul lifting, soaking you to the bone, crashing wave of gratitude and joy that is emanating from this group of people. There are SO many ways this team of people is banding together, ideating, taking action, sharing, and LIFTING our customers (and each other) in this incredible hectic time! I just want to take a moment to say thank you for working through this time of uncertainty with your hearts on your sleeve. For reaching out to customers and giving them strength and light and the power to do good. If there was ever a team meant for the right now, it's this team. Thank you from leading from each of your seats and for creating incredible opportunities on a daily basis for our customers, for our brand, and for our business! You're ALL HEART and I'm loving it!!!\n\n194#But also Respect for Urgency, Respect For all, etc|Hey Jill, I wanted to throw some #madprops your way for handling the past few days and next-level back and forth that has come with them with agility and grace. As the new guy, I don't always know what's business-as-usual and what's above-and-beyond, but I'd have to be as thick as a brick to miss the extra effort you're putting in. Your positivity and openness to collaboration has inspired me to handle my (occasionally hectic) self with equal level-headedness, and I'm looking forward to keeping this party rolling.\n\n195#And Thank YOU, team!|I wanted to recognize you all for being a part of the amazing Healthcare Thank you Video we launched to our customers and social channels yesterday afternoon. This was both a great initiative to showcase our respect for our customers and all members in the healthcare industry, as well as such a great team collaboration. Each and every one of you played a crucial part in making this so successful.   I was personally excited and touched by this video since I have so many family members and close friends in the front lines, and I'm so excited to share with them to brighten their day!\n\n196#Well that was NOT in my 30/60/90 day plan! ...|Team - A quick thank you to celebrate being 60 days in together. You continue to adapt to the businesses needs and lead through uncertain times with a high demonstrated commitment to the priorities we've aligned on to grow the business - ie., Build the brand; Acquire new customer; Grow existing customers; and Build our culture through people. Although COVID was in NO ONE'S playbook, you rallied and risen to this new challenge by partnering with me on a slightly \"revised\" version of my 30/60/90 plan. This is having such a positive halo effect on our teams. Look forward to the next 30 days of the plan ... whatever that looks, and with confidence that if we need to write it 1 page, 1 day at a time - this is the team I'm excited to do it with. Stay healthy, human, and connected! With gratitude, -C\n\n197#Now that's what a call teamwork!|Jill, Jeff - what do you do when you lose power while working from home amidst COVID crisis? The only logical thing, drive to a colleague's house and work in their garage. True teamwork, determination, and grit. Amazing example of teamwork and commitment to the business and each other. With gratitude, C\n\n198#You Are A Warrior|We all know that you are a hard worker, but last week you went into an entirely new gear.  You worked tirelessly to keep groups aligned, you were quick to respond and executed at lighting speed, and you managed to do this all while keeping the customer needs front and center.  Thank you for stepping up as a leader to guide us through a tricky week and for showcasing what good marketing can look like during a  time of crisis.  I would go into any battle with you.  Bring. It. On.\n\n199#Demand Gen Strong|Team, this is long overdue!  I want to thank each of you for welcoming me to the team and taking time to help me get up to speed on all things Workhuman.  It‚Äôs such a pleasure to work on a team that is so supportive of one another.  Miss seeing you all everyday, but until we are back in the office, I look forward to the daily slack conversations and, of course, the dad jokes.\n\n200#What a Ride!|Jill - I have to call out the quick and strong partnership we have built over the past three weeks. It's been one crazy ride! We went from planning WHL customer acquisition, to 1% of payroll, to recognition in difficult times, to COVID-19, and finally to the amazing offer of Life Events and Conversations at no cost to customers.  That is 5 topics in three weeks. Each time required a quick pivot, realignment, and plan of action. I cannot say enough about your organization, communication, and attitude through all of this. I feel incredibly lucky to be working along side such talent and dedication. I know this team is headed for great things. Thank you Jill!\n\n201#Is it still Wednesday?|Team -  First, thank you - often and always.  Second, I want to acknowledge we are operating in unprecedented times. This can trigger feelings of discomfort and anxiety if you let it. But, I believe we are strong enough together to rally, support, and mobilize each other to overcome that potential because you all as leaders already have. Know that every moment of progress you‚Äôve made this week already illustrates your strength, determination, and grit.  In the broader context - none of us are guaranteed a tomorrow - COVID may exacerbate that mindset - but in reality this too shall pass and we all will be stronger from it - personally and professionally.  I believe in you. And I believe in us together. Our collective strengths to overcome and our true human spirit to persevere will best this.  I am honored to serve alongside you in the pursuit of our brand, our customers, and the greater community we serve.  Thank you for all your support, kindness, and compassion you've extended to me this week!  With gratitude, -C\n\n202#Stay connected!|Thank you all for your honest feedback, smart editing, inspiring ideas and perseverance in getting the customer communication out yesterday.  The first is always the hardest when we have to get the tone, template, style and length right. Kevin, your timely assistance and editing were key. Eileen, your help in getting to the point and sorting out the structure made it pop.  Traci, you bring a dose of humanity and energy and this was no exception.  (Hello Humans!) And Jill, without you we would have been lost.  Templates and email alias and lists...oh my!  You have the patience of a saint.  It will be so much easier from here!  I am grateful to work alongside such talented and passionate colleagues.  Thank you!\n\n203#Quick strike team|Hi all - thank you for your tireless collaboration today on all of the different email communications that we're putting out into the world. You've each been wonderful to work with - Jill and Z, providing clarity of direction; Lauren being quick with all the words; John, keeping the tasks organized and all of us on track... Great teamwork, respect for urgency and respect for quality all around. I love that amidst uncertainty - we can still shine! (yep, that was cheesy and i don't care)\n\n204#A Virtual First|Anne, Diane, Holly, Jeff, Jill, Kelsey and Kristen ‚Äì thank you so much for the call that turned into my first virtual birthday party ever! Talk about staying connected in times of uncertainty and virtual human moments that matter! You all are so thoughtful and caring. Today had the potential to be a bit glum between all the craziness that is COVID, the mandatory isolation and the dreary weather but you have made sure to add a whole lot of light and laughter into my day. Thanks for all the love and thoughtfulness ‚Äì I have certainly felt it! Best. Teammates. Ever.\n\n205#It's Go Time!|Team - I wanted to first say thank you for your rapid response to the business's need for a COVID rapid response campaign. I also want to acknowledge that working at this pace and with a level of uncertainty may be new and/or uncomfortable, but that has not stopped this group from leaping into action, mobilizing, and being agile and responsive to rapidly evolving priorities - including stopping existing work, pivoting planned content, and being open-minded about new ways of working team together and team apart (as we leverage remote technology for the next while). Still lots to do, and I'm confident with the cohesion demonstrated this week we will do great things that help our current and future customers navigate uncertain times and that we will unlock new approaches and agility as a cross functional team. Thank you all. With gratitude, -C\n\n206#First Class Collaboration|Team! I wanted to say congratulations and celebrate the collaboration that infused our FY20 Marketing Strategy Board. As of this past Friday we have an aligned, crisp, and clear plan for Marketing's focus and KPIs that sits perfectly between the Company's goals, objectives, and major priorities. I also want to recognize the diligence that went into to making this be a plan that effectively spans Customer + Brand Marketing and reflects alignment with our key partners (SLT, CS, CX, and Finance). It is metrics driven to ensure accountability and through it's more streamlined nature, now infinitely more shareable with our teams and partners. Look forward to rolling this out to the teams through all hands these next two weeks and continuing to revisit it for focus, alignment, and relevance to the business's needs as our business evolves. Love to see the positive momentum and teamwork modeled to produce this output - lets keep it going. With gratitude, -C\n\n207#New Hire Celebration!|Jill - congratulations on your new *AMAZING* hire, Jeff Ellis! Thank you so much for being an incredible partner from start to finish - from providing me with industry insight and knowledge at our initial kick off, to your optimism and thoughtful consideration throughout the phone screening and interview process, and your quick, transparent cadence. For all of these reasons and then some, we were able to make this quality hire in a mere 18 days since req approval! I am so excited to see the successes Jeff accomplishes on your team, and cannot wait to work with you again in the future!\n\n208#Schneider Slam!|What a journey this has been. We first thought about how we could personalise and target Schneider executives and teams for WHL back in November, an idea was quickly weaponised with amazing collaboration, velocity and passion from Jill, Kristen and Kelsey. Our ability to be agile and pivot around our clients, not to be afraid to try new approaches and making things happen are virtues we seek everyday as humans. How fortunate I am that I am aligned to such a great team. We have had a massive response from Schneider and they are super excited about WHL this year. Thank you for the great work you all do and here's to the next initiative!\n\n209#November 21, 2019|Assuming Outlook is accurate, November 21, 2019  was our first official \"Marketing Directors meeting.\" Sixteen weeks later, I wanted to take a moment to personally thank each of you for ALLLL the time and energy you've invested in our time together. We've been meeting on a weekly basis  to establish more visibility, create more alignment across functional teams, collaborate on short and long term planning, negotiate budgets, brainstorm core marketing themes, discuss better ways of working together...the list goes on an on. And while I know we all cringe at the thought of another meeting on our calendars when we are starved for time, I strongly believe if we come together on a regular basis and focus on the right things, we'll all be smarter for it. I have so much gratitude for each of you! Thank you and see you next Wednesday!\n\n210#Last minute ask|On top of your day jobs, I asked each of you to present in our weekly marketing directors+ meeting today - without a ton of notice. You produced slides, shared great content, and kept the team engaged during your sessions. Thank you for embracing the new format for our weekly meeting which we tried for the first time today, and contributing to what felt like one of our best meetings to date!\n\n211#\"Celebrating\" Takeda|A huge THANK YOU and CONGRATULATIONS to this team for getting the Takeda contract over the goal line!  I have felt so privileged and inspired to work with each of you throughout this process. Tim, you truly defined what it means to be a great partner both Takeda and myself.  The trust you have built with them is beyond measure!  Steve, this has been a wild ride and your partnership has been invaluable.  From moment one you truly listened, came to the table with creative approaches and showed Takeda  and myself nothing but respect. Hillary, we have been joined at the hip since Baxalta!  It has been a roller coaster since this partnership started and you were there in a moment‚Äôs notice, incredibly focused on helping us get to the right result and a true class act!  Michael, I honestly couldn‚Äôt have made it through the RFP process without you.  You bring such a positive attitude and make a very daunting task enjoyable just by being you.  Like I have always said, no big deals get done in this company without you.  Greg, you always bring insights and a vision that are irrefutable.  No matter what the challenge, you brought a fresh perspective, helped to define the true story at Takeda and help to differentiate Workhuman.  Jill, you brought so much energy and positivity to this process.  You jumped right in to help bring Workhuman to life for Takeda.  Lots of back and forth to help us get the LinkedIn ads perfect, the microsite perfect, our communications to executives perfect.. just all of it.  Kristen, you came to the table saying, ‚Äúhow can I help?‚Äù and your partnership was invaluable.  You brought so many things to life that delivered true impact.  Eileen, you truly define what ‚Äútrue leadership‚Äù means.  You have been so supportive, walking alongside me, moving obstacles, having my back and beyond through this journey.  You believed in me at times in which I most certainly wavered through this process - incredible!\n\n212#Customers Belong at WHLive!|Dear Dream Team,   I am thankful for the opportunity to have worked with each of you this past quarter. All of you provided great insight into the Workhuman Live conference culture, shared past experiences, and areas we (Customer Success) could use to level set on our approach to pitching Workhuman Live to customers. Patrick, you shot it out the park with the WHLive Elevator Pitch Builder. This great exercise will help verbalize our thoughts regarding the importance of this conference. With that said, Tim, you absolutely captured the audience with your honesty and brought the facts to back up why Customers no matter the level or location should join in the WH movement. Judith, you are right! There is no wrong time to introduce WHLive and we should use our excitement from past conferences fuel customers to register. Dan, you took the time to review all the PowerPoints, documents, created a presentation timeline, lead meetings, and kept us on our toes. Furthermore, you didn‚Äôt mind answering my million questions on the presentation deck.   Jill and Jeff, thank you for creating the WHLive playbook deck. This resource which includes customer testimonials will truly help us with recruitment.   Couldn‚Äôt leave out our leaders, Danielle and Liz. You both prioritized our team meetings, listened to us gather our thoughts, and boldly asked us to reconsider our approaches for a centralized recruitment method. Without your guidance, this wouldn‚Äôt have been possible.   What I learned from working with this team is that we truly live and are fueled by the Workhuman experience with the common goal of inspiring other companies to reconsider the future of work. Excited to hear all the Moments that Matter at this years WHLive!   Sincerely, Kel\n\n213#Feeling connected|Pam and Jill - I wanted to say thank you for the warm welcome you've both provided to me as I made the move into the Customer Marketing team this quarter. Not only do I feel a personal connection strengthening between us, I feel our work is becoming more and more connected which is exactly part of our vision! You've both been proactively bringing me into various discussions and meetings and totally receptive to my ideas. As you know, Eric B and I often joked that we were often forgotten in our previous Product Marketing roles. There was some truth behind the joking. We had each other but I never truly felt like part of a team and now, I do - thanks in large part to you both! I hope you agree that we are getting into a good groove and are happy about the progress we're making on our strategic marketing plan. I am very excited to partner with you and the rest of our group to bring the plan to life and accomplish amazing things together this year. Go Team!!\n\n214#Best First 30 Days Ever!|Team - I was reflecting on how much we've accomplished during our first month together. I selected Urgency for this note because it best reflects what all of you have demonstrated - ie., the asap tackling of tough challenges with a sense of Shoshin (ÂàùÂøÉ) a word from Zen Buddhism meaning \"beginner's mind.\" To me this means displaying an attitude of openness, eagerness, and lack of preconceptions when studying a subject, even when studying at an advanced level, just as a beginner would. This truly captures the dynamic we've co-built and are accelerating progress in. A quick recap of five significant things we've accomplished together: 1.) Alignment with cross functional partners (SLT, CS/CX, and MLT); 2.) Re-organizing to achieve FY20 priorities and accelerate growth; 3.) Moving the needle toward stronger, crisper, more provocative marketing messages; 4.) As leaders, together, building a shared model of transparency, trust, and robust debate; and 5.) Leveling up to strategic joint business planning. In ways big and small you have made me feel welcome, informed, and more self-aware of how to build a successful team. Jill from our dine around and leadership on Demand 2.0, to Pam with your advice on language for positioning the re-org, to Jeff from your \"get it done and here's what I need from you clarity\" on all things WHL audience acquisition and shared love of sarcasm, to Z your willingness to be the glue between teams and dedicate source for Girl Scout cookies - I want to say thank you for all we've done together and a \"save\" a future thank you for all we will do together. Happy Friday to all - keep up the great human work - it matters. With gratitude, -C\n\n215#Shoutout to all my Saucy Aunts|Thank you all so much for bringing great energy, enthusiasm, and attention to the kickoff with Influitive! This was a true cross-functional effort with representation from CX, CS, Strategy and Consulting, Marketing, Sales Operations, and Design ‚Äì an awesome demonstration of the power of collaboration. As we heard, even our Influitive consultant was impressed with how much involvement we had. You all brought unique perspectives on how we can engage with and deliver value to our customers through this community platform. I‚Äôm still riding the wave of excitement coming from our kickoff and am so excited to engage with each of you further in executing on the strategy we developed together. And not only were we productive, but we got to have some fun in there too ?. I‚Äôm so grateful to work alongside each and every one of you. Looking forward to the amazing things to come!\n\n216#People-First Leadership|Team - I wanted to recognize the effort that went into our recent Customer Marketing re-alignment. Driven by and reflective of your input and support we implemented changes that were perceived positively by the business, and by - putting people first and considering the human aspects involved in change - have been received positively as growth and on-strategy changes by the great humans that make up the Customer Marketing organization. I thought it was important to celebrate this moment, because change is often scary, especially for teams in flux - but your advice and guidance around putting people first (always) directly influenced a plan that was highly communicative, well-scheduled, and well-executed by all involved. We are well on our way to the modernization of our Customer Marketing function. Thank you for building strong relationships on this journey - I'm optimistic they will pay dividends throughout FY20 and beyond! With gratitude, -C\n\n217#Full Speed Ahead|#weworkhuman #shootthemoon #theinstitute  What a revitalizing day and a half! Thank you to this team of great big thinkers and risk takers for a deeply challenging few days of daring to reach for BIG ideas and creative paths to accomplish our mission. It was a great way to kick off our ‚Äúproject‚Äù for 2020. I believe this team, in this partnership, can achieve new heights. Thank you for giving yourself to this with your whole self! Cheers to the Dream State! Special shouts to Becky, Traci, and Jill for helping nail down our process and making sure we paused to drink and eat!!!\n\n218#PUMPED!!! About Partnership ...|Jill, Pam - Thank you for your leadership on our Marketing Calendar Alignment workshop with SLT, CS, and CX Leaders today. This moment mattered today and will pay dividends continuously in FY20. I want to specifically recognize a thoughtful, well-prepared set of meeting materials and discussion guide. It generated a high level of engagement and participation from our partners, and created the basis for a strong go-forward platform for iterating, evolving, and delivering a dynamic Marketing plan that is on strategy, aligned with our sellers' and customers' needs, and explicitly linked to our business goals. It also reflected critical transparency and collaboration dynamics we are building cross-functionally. Thank you, well done, and excited about the momentum we have going. With gratitude, -C\n\n219#Feedback|Jill - Thank you so much for your feedback. These requests can be time consuming and challenging. I appreciate your thoughtful and candid feedback that I can action. I truly value our partnership and relationship!\n\n220#A Force Unlike Any Other!|A force.  There is no other way to describe Jill Crawford.  We had 30 people coming together for a hack-a-thon project, which I was running, and I suddenly could not be there.  ‚ÄòLife happened‚Äô to me, but you were right there to ensure that I could focus on my family and put me at ease that you had things in control.  The day went off without a hitch ‚Äì thanks to you.  And that‚Äôs just one example of Jill being Jill.  You have helped me with the teams program, customer proposals, media planning, strategizing, and execution.  Every day, I watch in awe at your ability to manage deliverables, give focus to the team, prioritize the dozens of initiatives we have, and so much more.  You give of yourself personally and professionally every day ‚Äì continuously offering a helping hand, advice, or just simply listening.  Your a manager, teammate, leader, friend ‚Äì and a true force behind us all.  I couldn‚Äôt do it without you!\n\n221#Project Bow Tie|Pam, Jill and Matt, I just wanted to call out the wonderful job you are doing with Project Bow Tie.  Reimagining our demand generation function is daunting.  But you managed Phase 1 so smoothly and we're starting to build some real momentum now.  Not only have you navigated through those ideal customer elements seamlessly, but you have kept all stakeholders well involved, informed and excited.  This type of innovation that brings together cross-functional teams and gets them all pulling in the same direction is a great example for how we will all have to act in the coming years to continue the company's growth and innovation.  We still have a long way to go but well done so far!\n\n222#Marketing Master and Elevate Champion|It is incredible you can balance so many things at once and were able to lead the entire Marketing department in total shares of LinkedIn content. Your hard work and effort is greatly appreciated!\n\n223#Wonder Woman and She Ra have competition!|Jill and Pam- Thank you so much for bringing us together today to share what you learned and walk us through an exercise that will enable us to be more successful as Marketers! Your willingness to share and maintain transparency makes you both GREAT leaders! I know I don‚Äôt speak for myself when I say ‚ÄúThank You‚Äù for allowing us to be a part of something amazing! If She Ra and Wonder Woman ever joined force they‚Äôd have some serious competition!\n\n224#Expert Guides|Thank you for guiding our teams through a fantastic planning session yesterday.  It was engaging, collaborative and fun.  As a result, we were able to ideate and let our creative juices flow.  I was particularly impressed with your approach to the session.  You constantly had the big picture in mind and guided the team to many important discoveries.  Thank you for using this