ig opportunities as an organization. Thank you for early and late meetings, for staying focused, and for caring so much about excellence! This has been an incredible 'test' of the WH network! Bravo!\n\n229#Q4 QBRs Rocked!|Thanks to every person on this team for bringing your best selves to Cleveland in the middle of a flurry of major projects, meetings, deliverables, and personal commitments. Each of you came together to share some incredible best practices, strategies that have moved the needles with our biggest opportunities, and some big plans for 2020. There is no better group of people to spend 2.5 days with talking about work. You bring a passion to the business that is only matched by Traci's passion for Cleveland! Thank you for your commitment to excellence! You ROCK!\n\n230#Co-creating Great CX is a Team Sport!|Dear Team, I am so grateful to be able to call upon this amazing group of people! You were each willing to invest an entire day to thinking through the customer lens as part of our journey mapping workshop.   To say that I am impressed with the progress we made is an understatement.  We now have 4 draft journey maps - current and dream state for two incredibly important customer types, the End User and Buyer! Thank you for your contribution, energy and excitement about what we are seeking to do and the impact this can have on our business goals!  As we shared, CX is owned by all humans at Workhuman and this team showed so much commitment to CX and excitement around the potential that exists that if this is an indicator of how the rest of the company will feel, it makes me even more excited about how fast we can move our CX from current state to intentional & differentiated!!! Thank you, thank you, thank you!!!  You guys ROCK!\n\n231#WH Live  - we hit our first milestone!!!!|Team,  I am so proud of, energized and inspired by each of you!  We have hit our first milestone!  Your creativity, dedication and action bias have been evident from day 1!   I tr