r campaign and post-event plan. From before Workhuman until now you've kept me in the loop, reminded me of upcoming deadlines, and have been a second set of eyes before each one goes out the door. Most importantly, you've both been a pleasure to collaborate with along the way.\n\n278#No more inquiries about inquiries|Thanks for leading a fantastic Lunch & Learn session for the marketing team.  Your presentation was engaging, well thought-out and very informative.  And, your conversational style made it easy to ask questions and get involved.   It's sessions like this - open, transparent, and clear -  that will help us work as one, cohesive unit rather than in small, disparate groups.   Thanks for taking time out of your busy schedules to put this together.\n\n279#Because you care|Today you refused to go to a kickoff. Not because you wanted to be a jerk, but because the brief lacked the detail it should have had and you care. What I want to recognize you for is the way you handled it. You offered your precious time to sit with the project owner to make sure she understood how to fill out a brief properly. You know going into that meeting today, not having that valuable information would have been a big miss and caused more meetings or for people to leave that meeting unsure if what they needed to do. We all need to support one another and get this Marketing team up and running smoothly. You are the best brief writer so that person should be thankful and will hopefully lean on you again in the future if she needs to, but I think you just taught someone a thing or two that will stick with them for a while. You just saved a lot of time and headache right there. I can‚Äôt wait to see her next brief. Thank you for getting others to do their best just as you do every single day!!!!\n\n280#Great partners for exploration!|Jill, Laura, Kristen - Sharing some gratitude with you all on your ongoing partnership. Jill, how you are able to manage the competing priorities and campaigns that have been put on your plate lately is OUTSTANDING. You are always looking for ways to up-level our work, and drive inquiry goals. As a team, you all approached me with some great ideas for emails and landing pages for Workhuman prospect/customer follow up. Thank you for being open to collaboration, and pushing to do something different. I'm really looking forward to learning how these perform, and working on a long-term approach as we go forward!\n\n281#Living our values|Appreciation and gratitude to both Kristen and Jill for pushing out an email send deadline which allowed me to participate fully in the Persona Training workshop.  We live and breathe our deadlines in marketing ops no matter what else is going on around us.  The decision to push out one deadline made a huge difference, allowing me to be fully present in valuable training today.  Thank you!\n\n282#Persona Workshop Warriors Unite!|I have such a grateful heart for this day, this entire team of Marketing mavens, and all the opportunities that sit within our reach. I have never felt more connected to our team than I do at this very moment. We just completed an all hands, all day persona workshop! Woohoo!!! Thank you for your investment. Thank you for being a kind audience that stayed engaged. Thank you for asking thoughtful questions. Thank you for your humor and your patience. Thank you for being real. Thank you for embracing the 7 1/2 hour marathon persona training session we shared today with gusto and heart! I truly believe that we will be a better team, and we will produce better marketing because of the time we spent together today. I can‚Äôt wait to hear your feedback about the agenda, the learning modules, the wiki‚Ä¶.ALL the things! I can‚Äôt wait to apply this first body of persona work to our marketing efforts. Let‚Äôs GOOOOOOO!\n\n283#Excellent Exec Readout - WH Live 2019|Hey team, I am so grateful for your professionalism and expertise, so clearly demonstrated in today's WH Live readout to the Exec Team. In many cases, team members dove deep, and you had all the answers because YOU KNOW YOUR STUFF. BAM! Well done, you made me proud!\n\n284#Barn & Noble Rock stars!|To the bookstore team...Thank you! I can't begin to describe how awesome this year's team was at Workhuman. Anthony, Jess and Mike, your ability to help anyone that needed it along with managing daily email sends and data clean up was awesome. Janet, Colleen, Maggie, and Manan...the best, most reliable back up crew a team could ask for! You never missed a call for support or a shift to help, from supporting customers, to learning Square, right down to stocking shelves, you made it possible for us to take breaks to see sessions, eat lunch, or manage the book signings. And then my steady crew - Liz, Maureen, Stephen, Wendy, John, and Jill, and Sara - these were long days on our feet, moving heavy books, and keeping customers happy. We were able to breakdown and pack up in record time thanks to you as well. You were all a joy to work with! Thank you all for the support and I hope you enjoyed Workhuman!\n\n285#Post event survey support|Thank you team for being a clear set of eyes on the last day to proof read and update the final attendee survey. We wanted to ensure our survey went out while the event was still fresh and clear in people's minds. Even though you were all busy, you made time on your schedules to give the survey one last clean review to ensure we caught all the important details. I appreciate your willingness to jump in and support the team and help us produce quality work!\n\n286#You guys rock!|Thank you all for being such amazing team members to our marketing team. We appreciate all you do from campaign planning, communication, collaboration, (oxford comma) and execution. Our operations team is only as strong as the team members we have working with us and you guys go above and beyond with each campaign. Thank you all for your attention to detail and working with Mike and Diane through the busy months of Workhuman and Demand Gen activities. We love working with you guys and value how hard each of you work to execute campaigns with a purpose. We all share laughs, tears, and excitement for every project. (JK on the tears) (Sometimes) (JK again!). I look forward to our future programs this summer! Keep up the great work y'all!\n\n287#Hitting the Workhuman numbers!|Jill, well done in exceeding our revised Workhuman audience numbers. I know the team worked incredibly hard, and we have lots to learn from this year - thank you for bringing it home and getting us over the line. No matter what, our growth YOY is impressive, and it would not have happened without your leadership. Thank you!\n\n288#Lead the Way!|Woah, that was fast! From conception to roll out it was less than 2 weeks to get the new lead retrieval solution out the door. Each of you provided such valuable insight and feedback. I can't wait to see the data that comes in!\n\n289#There's life after Nashville?|Dan, Jill, and Laura - While everyone is heads down preparing for Nashville, you are working hard on what looks like a kick-ass follow-up plan! Thank you for taking me (and  many others) through it over the last week to talk through 'all the things' - How does this impact Workhuman Cloud for Teams? How should sales and CS follow-up? What's the ABM strategy? Is the timing aggressive enough? Will this plan help progress opps?  It's shaping up beautifully with quite a few \"new and improved\" elements over previous years that will be exciting to test and see how attendees respond. Thank you for bringing a fresh, smart perspective to this important, time-sensitive initiative!\n\n290#Vitamin C|Is the juice worth the squeeze. You bet! This recognition is for getting every ounce of juice for Nashville. Working tirelessly to get every last message to every potential attendee - local, agenda, celebrities - you targeted all the profiles. Sharpening and re-sharpening the budget pencil 