t is related to the marketing of the event. While results have taken a disappointing turn you have kept the \"pedal to the metal\" and never wavered from making sure we are trying everything.  I am grateful to have you at the helm, ensuring that everyone is doing their utmost to make us as successful as possible.\n\n295#Fast, Accurate, Inspiring Hands|For all of you lasered focused on all of the varied communications going out to our customers, THANK YOU! It's a race to Nashville and I am SO happy to have you all on our team! Lots of details and first impressions to be made and you are all making every effort to knock them out of the park.  YOU ROCK!\n\n296#WorkHuman Wonder Woman|Jill, I can't say enough about how great of a business partner you have been over the past few months. You are juggling WorkHuman, Globoforce, and who knows how many other projects, and you tackle them all with grace and a willingness to pivot at the drop of the hat. For WorkHuman specifically, you are always willing to sit with me and answer questions or shoot over a slack so that things can keep moving along as fast as possible, and if you don't know an answer, you are able to get it within minutes. I really appreciate how committed and involved you have been in trying to develop a program that is both successful and sustainable for the future. Thank you!!\n\n297#Navigating the Winding Road of WorkHuman|Jill - I am grateful for your awesome work leading our Workhuman acquisition efforts. The captain of the ship!  The drive to Workhuman is far from easy.  Many twists and turns.  Many things out of our hands but you‚Äôve managed our collective efforts in a collaborative and respectful way. You always keep the key objectives in mind and always display a determination and passion to getting us toward our goal. You also make sure to lighten the mood when needed during tense meetings. This element is hugely important. We are all humans working toward a common goal and this level of empathy for your teammates goes a long way ‚Äì and drives better performance and teamwork.  Thank you.\n\n298#demand 2.0|It's really hard to find the time (never mind the head space) to think beyond the many looming deadlines we are juggling, so I want to thank you both for an invigorating discussion and a great working session this morning to reimagine how we manage demand gen as we grow and evolve. I think it was probably 9 months ago we really began to identify ways we can up our game and work toward a best practices model for demand, and while we have made some progress for sure, it's time to dig in. I love seeing the commitment to excellence combined with a pragmatic approach to improving how we engage with the market and support pipeline acceleration. We are early in the process but this work will help set the company and our team up for the next level of success. Let's keep going!\n\n299#Agile Awesome|Awesome work in coming together to announce Lisa Borders on our social channel. Process is extremely important - but there are sometimes occasions where we need to be agile and quick to take advantage of an opportunity. Agile thinking can also be a great opportunity to test and learn.  Many times the best learnings come from the untried. I look forward to seeing how the stagger approach works to announcing a speaker for WorkHuman.\n\n300#You Rock!|Hi Jill, Just a little note of thank you for our monthly Marketing Programs/BDR meetings. You are always honest and real with us, listen to us with an open mind,  keep us posted and have great ideas to move things forward. I so appreciate you! ~Allison\n\n301#Speakers, Data, Codes.....GO!|Thank you for coming together over the past week to review numbers, offer insights, provide support and develop and roll out a communication plan in 2 days time around our WH speakers and registration goals. Your efforts are vital to our company wide messaging and the success of WorkHuman registrations over the next few weeks. Thanks for making this all come together for our company-wide announcement and action plan!\n\n302#100% effort, 100% to goal!|Congrats on achieving the 20,000 inquiry goal for 2018 ‚Äî a valuable and engaged universe of campaign respondents that will drive future value for Globoforce! What's more, over the past year we've worked together to become both smarter and more efficient in how we plan, execute and measure demand campaigns. The advent of Core campaigns for Recognition and Performance means we have a consistent presence using less team resources, the digital component is more thoughtful and effective and we are tuning up and optimizing wherever we can. 2019 is sure to be another big step up; thank you for the great work!\n\n303#Stellar Survey Promotions|Thanks to this talented team for successfully promoting the Customer Satisfaction (NPS) Survey.  Without your engaging content, accurate dashboards and timely execution we couldn‚Äôt have received the number of responses that we did (especially during such a noisy time of year for our customers).   The more responses we get, the better we understand our customers and the better we can meet their needs. Thank you!\n\n304#The little engine that could|I am not sure where we would be without you, but thank you for jumping in to do another job besides your own, and helping to organize and manage campaigns and special efforts for the marketing of WorkHuman. Your enthusiasm, organization and imagination have been so instrumental in helping us to reach 1400 registrants - and I know will help us to reach the finish line. Thank you for your long hours and extra efforts for the team, and for keeping everyone and everything on track.\n\n305#Q4 2018 North America Social Media Champions|Congrats all of you on being the top sharers of our social media posts on Dynamic Signal for Q4! Your added boost to our content gets our thought leadership in front of more potential customers and employees. Thank you for your help!\n\n306#Just because...you're so amazing!|Jill, I've been meaning to give you this award for a while now. You've taken on so much of the WorkHuman load this year. You lead meetings with a purpose and have helped to streamline many lengthy processes. All of us notice your tremendous efforts and you've been a wonderful teammate to collaborate with on content and speaker highlights. This is a \"respect for all\" award because you always have respect for quality, urgency, and teamwork.\n\n307#You nailed it!|Jill, congratulations on the terrific job you did in this weeks' Exec meeting. You were calm, cool and collected,  even when delivering an important update on one of our biggest challenges - WH05 audience acquisition! I just love your wonderful combination of pleasant disposition, humour and high standards - it's been delightful to watch you take on more responsibilities and whip us all into shape. Keep on keeping on!\n\n308#Working Human, Working Smart = Big Results!|Hey team, I wanted to acknowledge the great progress you have all made in just a few short weeks. From getting more data to better understanding registration sources and drivers, to launching an incredibly successful Cyber Monday campaign, it feels like every week the team gets savvier, more disciplined and more effective. You are a living demonstration of the power of \"working smart\" vs. just \"working hard\". I can't wait to see even more insights and intelligence as we continue to learn and optimize!\n\n309#Journeymapping Stars!|A sincere thank you on behalf of the CX Team for participating in our first ever journeymapping aimed at the buyers experience. Each of you represented core areas of our business and stepped into the shoes of our customers to provide deep insights to create a picture in time of our current state. Journeymapping is an extensive project that requires many! Every single phase of the journey is critical to our business, from first awareness to contracting‚Ä¶ from launch to even potential shut downs. Thank you so much for your passionate participation and honest candor. It's a pretty amazing thing that we have to remind folks to table brainstorming or solutions so that we can first nail down the current state. To me, this shows how eager our people are to learn from our past, dip into research and data, to push the boundaries on innovation and to challenge the status quo so that Globoforce can be way above the pack. These sessions and your input will propel us forward in every single corner of the business to be more aware and aligned with each other and with our customers. That is powerful - THANK YOU!\n\n310#At the helm!|It's the eve of THANKSgiving and you Jill are top of mind. I wanted to pause before the rush and send my appreciation for you and all you have done for the customer side of the house. It feels like you have been working for Globoforce for many years. The amount of things you have joined Alice and I on as it relates to customers and then impacted greatly is something others were not able to do in a much longer period of time. You have \"graceful grit\" and such a huge heart. I am so so very happy that we snagged you for Globoforce because you have been phenomenal to work with and have helped us to align projects and actions where they belong. I know the sky is the limit now because we have you at the helm. THANK YOU for being you and delivering A+ to our team and our customers. We have felt the impact in so many ways and this is just the beginning. :)\n\n311#Superwoman|Jill, I wanted to take a moment to acknowledge just how amazing you are. You are managing so many things right now, are being pulled in so many directions, are advising on so many initiatives ‚Äì I don‚Äôt know how you manage to keep it all straight! And what‚Äôs more, everything you touch seems to turn to gold. Your insights are invaluable and the impact you‚Äôve had on our team, department and company are truly impressive. And what‚Äôs more, you‚Äôre extremely responsive, and always make time to check-in with me which I appreciate more than you know. Thanks for being a superwoman boss!\n\n312#We're getting better - since you've been ours!|Jill - Your hard work and dedication to understanding and revamping the WorkHuman audience acquisition team's approach to planning and execution has been paramount as of late. These past few weeks, as we inch closer and closer to the \"double down\" zone have been a whirlwind. Updates, pulling reports, analyzing promotions for the past 4 WorkHumans, rethinking existing campaigns, strategizing news ones, and optimizing.optimizing.optimizing. I KNOW it hasn't been easy. And I know that you are surprisingly still fairly new to all of this but, I can say, we're certainly getting better all the time thanks to your leadership. You've taken the time to get to know each team member's roles and responsibilities, workloads, strengths and weaknesses and you're using all that information (and more) to steer us towards our goals without burning out. And without forgetting your \"day job\" ;) Thank you for everything. Especially for still being able to make us laugh when we need it!\n\n313#Together we have achieved greatness!|Thank you all so much for your incredible partnership delivering the NPS customer close the loop communication. It was definitely a tough project at times as we navigated the options available to us in order to ensure the first piece was delivered correctly to maximize the impact on the customers. The content was obviously a key ingredient. We had to take a huge amount of very detailed content from across many departments and massage it into impactful, meaningful and valuable nuggets that the clients would value and would allow the customer to be inspired about how well we are listening to them and acting upon their feedback with the net result being their decision to participate in the next survey and rate us with a higher NPS score!  No small feat!  Yes, we learned a lot to bring to the next phase 