k together!\n\n317#WorkHuman Wonder Women|Ladies, I just want to acknowledge all the work you're doing to make sure the marketing/creative side of WH 2019 continues to run smoothly. It's not an easy job, but the three of you are managing it with efficiency, grace, thoughtfulness, creativity, and humor - as always. You rock!\n\n318#Marketing Leadership at Work!|Big Team - thank you for all the hard work and homework you put into preparing for the Marketing Offsite. It took weeks of prep, but we plowed through the entire organizational plan AND gave ourselves space for some extraordinarily creative and transformational thinking (who doesn't love THAT? ;-) Thank you for bringing your whole selves and giving your colleagues the gift of your undivided attention. Thank you for your leadership, candor and trust, and thank you for your DECADES AND DECADES of experience, put to work! :-)  As we all know, the real hard work starts now to get us to coherent and aligned 2019 plans, executing against those plans and tackling the big projects we identified. I am so proud to be a part of this team, and I meant what I said: I have NEVER worked with a more engaged group of people in my entire career. I am so excited about what we will accomplish together, and how we will contribute to accelerating Eric's thrilling vision for our company!\n\n319#Bringing out the Inner Peace!|Thank you for making the exercise of taping my very first video shoot a great experience!  You were so kind, sensitive and helpful in ensuring I felt comfortable and could do the best to deliver in the moment!  Thank you!  You are such pro's and you made it way more fun than I expected, even though doing it in the kitchen was super scary with all the activity and humans roaming around in there!  Great work and thank you!  PS - love the teleprompter! :-)\n\n320#Newsletter take 2!|Awesome work on the quarterly \"low touch\" customer newsletter. Thank you all for the different roles that you played, from helping with the verbiage, to the creative, to the sending, and to the overall vision and completion of this once again. I appreciate all of the help, and it wouldn't have come to be without all of you!\n\n321#Excellent September All Hands!|Team, thank you so much for your individual and collective efforts to deliver yet another technically flawless, engaging and informative Marketing All Hands. These times we get together to share our progress and connect with one another are so important to our strength as a team. Thank you for bringing your best selves and taking the time to communicate with your colleagues!\n\n322#Great Partners|Thank you each for sharing part of your busy week with the SCD team for our Q3/2019 ideation and planning sessions. Each of you make a huge impact on our work with customers every day and each of you truly understand what it means to partner. We‚Äôre so lucky to have partners who share our optimism, vision for growth, and impatience for all of the opportunities we want to close in on! Many thanks for sharing you time and talent in person (!) this week. Sincerely appreciated!\n\n323#Analyze This!|Jill ‚Äì Since you‚Äôve started at Globoforce, you‚Äôve been a dynamo.  You‚Äôve quickly become such a trusted and reliable leader on so many fronts.  I also wanted to highlight your work  with our industry analysts.  These are important people to us ‚Äì relationships that have long-term significance. Collaborating with us and them on lead gen programs is incredibly useful toward showing Globoforce's commitment to them and leveraging our relationship on the sales side. Thank you for making programs happen with these folks (it began with Brandon Hall but upcoming plans are set too!).  It‚Äôs a pleasure working with you on these projects and strategies!\n\n324#Pivot to present in hours|Taking a minute to recognize my teammates on the Agency Workflow priority. Monday afternoon we had to pivot and rework our presentation with a tight deadline. This team jumped 