y what needs to come through in the campaigns you are building! Every time I had another version to share with you, no matter how busy you were, you jumped in to suggest different ways of saying or structuring something. Your feedback was extremely useful and I'm excited to continue our collaboration. Thank you for being awesome teammates with great attitudes and ideas.\n\n334#5th dimension beyond that which is known to man...|... it is a dimension as vast as space and as timeless as infinity...  it's called TOP OF FUNNEL.  Tactics, types, segments, strategies, nurturing, goals, inquiries, conversions... as I was thinking of these words, admittedly the twilight zone spiral came to mind.  Demand Gen and top of funnel marketing is a world of it's own; a delicate partnership between Sales, Operations and ABM.  You four foxes have played a pivotal role in ensuring our programs are designed and executed flawlessly.  The dynamic and communication among this group is untouchable; and I'm so proud to roll with such an intelligent pack of women.  Hey!  ... that's the signpost up ahead - your next stop, OPPORTUNITY!   :)\n\n335#A focus on Conversations|While a number of important marketing initiatives have supported Conversations since launch, until recent weeks we haven't had the opportunity or the bandwidth to come together as a team with a cohesive plan to increase awareness, drive demand and better supports the sales and customer success teams. The plan we presented this week is a framework we can build on to better reach the market with a compelling message, and to communicate across marketing and with sales. The planning process got us moving and shines a light on where we need to focus. Thank you all for making the time to contribute with already very full schedules --  a special shout out to Eric B for shepherding the team to get this done!\n\n336#The heart of Globoforce|Jill and Laura, Can we please take a second to recognize all of your efforts to keep Globoforce pumping through everyone‚Äôs veins? We have a steady heartbeat of beautifully designed assets being worked on between multiple programs at a constant rate. The results you share keep our hearts full. The number of webinar registrants you pull in are amazing! Thank you for all of your planning, organization and updates as things move and change to ensure everyone stays on track. Your hearts are truly in it!\n\n337#Inspiring our Customers!|Thank you all for helping put together what was THE BEST customer webinar we've held to date!  It took a lot of herding cats, a lot of follow up, some technical skills, and a lot of creative editing and each of you pitched in with joyful hearts!  The UHG team knocked it out of the park and it could not have happened without all of you tee'ing them up for success!  Bravo!!!!!!!!\n\n338#the perfect pairing|You guys go together like peanut butter and chocolate‚Äìand you just make everything better! I wanted to give you both a shout out for all the work, the organizing and planning, putting up with me constantly poking everything with a stick, last minute edits and approvals‚Äìit's been a project to say the least! But you two have handled it with grace and determination. I feel like we're set up for success because of all the hard work you two have been doing and I know it's going to get us to a better place. I cannot wait to see how these new campaigns perform, but I know it's only the beginning and it will set the benchmark for all of us. Thank you for all the value that you add, your partnership and your patience!!!!\n\n339#Thanks for the chatter!|Jill- Thank you so much for taking time out of your busy day- before vacation no less to walk me through the marketing plan for conversations. Matt reached out to me and on the fly I created a plan that made no sense. After sitting with you I realized that there is a solid plan already in place. I was able to give you his T10/S25 to help with some digital and social targeting done by our third parties and will regroup with him to discuss a creative foot opening approach- possible some chatter teeth? (I hear Pam cringing lol) Thank you for helping a fellow teammate out!\n\n340#A commitment to getting it right|In typical Globoforce fashion the launch of the RAP campaign was a great team effort, but I want to call out your leadership of the project and the quality of the result. It is such a good step forward to see a coordinated effort with a series of related messages against different personas and a cohesive experience through the campaign journey. You've done a terrific job of communicating across the team -- and making sure the issues were well understood and that we kept on moving forward! Your responsiveness, focus and great sense of humor all made a big difference (and do every day)! Look forward to seeing the results in market and learning from the effort!\n\n341#Bootcamp Prep!|Hey team, thank you so much for all your time and effort in prepping me to speak to our demand gen/lead gen/social selling/campaign attribution efforts at last weeks' Sales Bootcamp. Feedback was very positive, and it's so great to see the ongoing tight relationship between Marketing and Sales. Looking forward to more great results in 2H and beyond!\n\n342#Carrier Pigeons|Thank you both for all your help in getting me the links I needed to send a prospect. She had lost the information and really wanted to be able to experience all the speakers again from WorkHuman and you made it happen. Thank you.\n\n343#Q2 Social Media sharing champions!|Joyce and Jill - Congrats on your 1st and 2nd place finish in the VoiceStorm social media sharing standings. You've both embraced our content and set a great example in amplifying it to your networks. Thanks and congrats!\n\n344#Ready for your close up!|In true Globoforce fashion, when I put the call out for photoshoot models, so many people jumped at the chance to help. A photoshoot like the one we held this week takes true teamwork and 