r ability to take all of these variables, pull them into a plan, and work with the broader team to execute is super impressive. I truly appreciate all of your efforts and your dedication! Keep up the great work!\n\n357#Q1 Social Champions|Congrats on being one of the top social sharers for Q1 through VoiceStorm! Thank you for embracing this technology and helping us spread the word about our great activities!\n\n358#Resources for Resources|This is a bit overdue, but thank you all for the various critical roles you all played in getting our new online Resource Center launched.  When we kicked off, the vendor told us it was generally a 8-12 week launch period.  They hadn't met THIS marketing department yet!  From integrating with existing systems to troubleshooting forms to creating, organizing, and entering content, you all took this project to heart and helped get us online in 3 weeks!  It was truly a mad dash and you all pulled out all the stops.  Great work and thank you!\n\n359#Action Plans in Action|WorkHuman generates a buzz that gives us an enormous opportunity to follow up with prospects and customers. Each of you went above and beyond to create the Action Plans and breakout session PDFs that were emailed today. Timing was extremely important as we needed to get these out this week for optimal impact. Lauren B and Aaron ‚Äì thanks for your smart copy. Lauren C, Brian, and Matt ‚Äì thanks for scrambling to get the session PDFs uploaded in a timely fashion. Amanda ‚Äì thanks for your wonderful eye for design. Carrie ‚Äì thanks for providing photos so quickly. Alice and Kevin ‚Äì thanks for your input and edits. Anthony ‚Äì thanks for your Marketo expertise to get the emails properly targeted. Jill ‚Äì thanks for your sales communication. And Lauren C and Amanda ‚Äì double thanks for scrambling to correct the multiple PDFs that had to be resized at the 11th hour. Crazy week, crazy day ‚Äì excellent result. Thank you.\n\n360#Agile Follow Up Team|S/O to all of you